<eesti>&sect; 1. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 1. </inglise>
<eesti>Seaduse objekt </eesti>
<inglise>Purpose of Act </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esolev seadus m&auml;&auml;rab Eesti maksus&uuml;steemi, maksuseadustele esitatavad n&otilde;uded, maksumaksja, maksu kinnipidaja, garandi ja maksuhalduri &otilde;igused, kohustused ja vastutuse ning maksuvaidluste lahendamise korra. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) This Act specifies the Estonian tax system, the requirements for tax Acts, the rights, duties and liability of taxpayers, withholding agents, guarantors and tax authorities, and the procedure for resolution of tax disputes. </inglise>
<eesti>(10.04.96 j&otilde;ust.12.05.96 - RT I 1996, 29, 577) </eesti>
<inglise>(10.04.96 entered into force 12.05.96 - RT I 1996, 29, 577) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esolevas seaduses s&auml;testatut rakendatakse k&otilde;ikide maksude suhtes, kui maksuseaduses endas ei n&auml;hta ette maksu iseloomust tulenevaid erieeskirju. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The provisions of this Act apply to all taxes unless a tax Act prescribes specific rules arising from the nature of the tax. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 2. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 2. </inglise>
<eesti>M&otilde;isted </eesti>
<inglise>Definitions </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esolevas seaduses kasutatakse m&otilde;isteid j&auml;rgmises t&auml;henduses: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In this Act, the following definitions are used: </inglise>
<eesti>1) maks - maksuseadusega v&otilde;i seaduse alusel antud kohaliku omavalitsus&uuml;ksuse volikogu m&auml;&auml;rusega riigi ja kohaliku omavalitsuse avalik-&otilde;iguslike &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmiseks v&otilde;i selleks vajaliku tulu saamiseks maksumaksjale pandud etten&auml;htud korras, suuruses ja t&auml;htp&auml;evadel ilma otsese vastutasuta t&auml;itmisele kuuluv rahaline kohustis. </eesti>
<inglise>1) "tax" means a financial obligation imposed on taxpayers by an Act concerning a tax or by a local government council regulation issued pursuant to an Act for the performance of the public law functions of the state and local governments or to obtain revenue required therefor and which is subject to performance pursuant to the procedure, in the amount and on the due dates prescribed, without direct compensation therefor. </inglise>
<eesti>Rahaline kohustis, millel pole k&otilde;iki eelmainitud tunnuseid, ei ole k&auml;esoleva seaduse t&auml;henduses maks; </eesti>
<inglise>A financial obligation which does not have all of the aforementioned attributes is not a tax for the purposes of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>(12.04.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.04.2000 entered into force 01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </inglise>
<eesti>2) maksuseadus - eraldi seadus, millega s&auml;testatakse konkreetne maks; </eesti>
<inglise>2) "Act concerning a tax" means a separate Act which provides for a specific tax; </inglise>
<eesti>3) maksumaksja - f&uuml;&uuml;siline v&otilde;i juriidiline isik, samuti riigi-, valla- v&otilde;i linnaasutus, kes maksuseadusega s&auml;testatud tingimustel ning seadusega v&otilde;i selle alusel antud kohaliku omavalitsus&uuml;ksuse volikogu m&auml;&auml;rusega s&auml;testatud korras on kohustatud maksu maksma, v&otilde;i v&otilde;lgnik tolliseadustiku m&otilde;istes; </eesti>
<inglise>3) "taxpayer" means a natural or legal person, or a state, rural municipality or city agency, who is required to pay tax under the conditions provided for in an Act concerning a tax and pursuant to the procedure provided for in an Act or a local government council regulation issued pursuant to an Act, or a debtor within the meaning of the Customs Code; </inglise>
<eesti>(17.10.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.07.2002 - RT I 2001, 88, 531) </eesti>
<inglise>(17.10.2001 entered into force 01.07.2002 - RT I 2001, 88, 531) </inglise>
<eesti>4) maksu kinnipidaja - f&uuml;&uuml;siline v&otilde;i juriidiline isik, samuti riigi-, valla- v&otilde;i linnaasutus, kes maksuseaduses s&auml;testatud tingimustel ja korras on kohustatud maksu kinni pidama ja maksuhalduri pangakontole kandma; </eesti>
<inglise>4) "withholding agent" means a natural or legal person, or a state, rural municipality or city agency, who is required to withhold a tax and transfer the tax to the bank account of the tax authority under the conditions and pursuant to procedure provided for in an Act concerning a tax; </inglise>
<eesti>(12.04.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.04.2000 entered into force 01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </inglise>
<eesti>5) (Kehtetu - 17.02.99 j&otilde;ust.01.04.99 - RT I 1999, 27, 394) </eesti>
<inglise>5) (Repealed - 17.02.99 entered into force 01.04.99 - RT I 1999, 27, 394) </inglise>
<eesti>6) maksudeklaratsioon - tulu-, k&auml;ibe- v&otilde;i tollideklaratsioon, maksuaruanne v&otilde;i muu maksu suuruse arvutamiseks etten&auml;htud dokument, mille maksumaksja v&otilde;i maksu kinnipidaja on maksuseaduse v&otilde;i tolliseadustiku alusel kohustatud esitama maksuhaldurile; </eesti>
<inglise>6) "tax return" means an income tax return, value-added tax return, customs declaration, annual tax report or other document prescribed for the calculation of tax, and which a taxpayer or withholding agent is required, pursuant to an Act concerning a tax or the Customs Code, to submit to a tax authority; </inglise>
<eesti>(17.10.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.07.2002 - RT I 2001, 88, 531) </eesti>
<inglise>(17.10.2001 entered into force 01.07.2002 - RT I 2001, 88, 531) </inglise>
<eesti>7) maksuv&otilde;lg - maksumaksja poolt t&auml;htp&auml;evaks tasumata v&otilde;i maksu kinnipidaja poolt t&auml;htp&auml;evaks &uuml;le kandmata j&auml;etud maksusumma, t&auml;htp&auml;evaks tasumata v&otilde;i &uuml;le kandmata j&auml;etud maksusummalt arvestatud intress ja tolliv&otilde;last tulenev t&auml;htp&auml;evaks tasumata maksusumma ning sellelt arvestatud intress; </eesti>
<inglise>7) "tax arrears" means tax which a taxpayer has failed to pay or which a withholding agent has failed to transfer by the due date, interest calculated on tax unpaid or not transferred by the due date, or the amount of a customs debt unpaid by the due date and interest calculated on such amount; </inglise>
<eesti>(10.04.96 j&otilde;ust.12.05.96 - RT I 1996, 29, 577; 12.04.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </eesti>
<inglise>(10.04.96 entered into force 12.05.96 - RT I 1996, 29, 577; 12.04.2000 entered into force 01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </inglise>
<eesti>8) (Kehtetu - 12.04.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </eesti>
<inglise>8) (Repealed - 12.04.2000 entered into force 01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </inglise>
<eesti>9) maksuv&otilde;la tasumise ajatamine - maksuv&otilde;la tasumise ajakava kehtestamine maksumaksja taotlusel; </eesti>
<inglise>9) "postponement of payment of tax arrears" means the establishment of a schedule for the payment of tax arrears at the request of the taxpayer; </inglise>
<eesti>(10.04.96 j&otilde;ust.12.05.96 - RT I 1996, 29, 577) </eesti>
<inglise>(10.04.96 entered into force 12.05.96 - RT I 1996, 29, 577) </inglise>
<eesti>10) (Kehtetu - 12.04.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </eesti>
<inglise>10) (Repealed - 12.04.2000 entered into force 01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </inglise>
<eesti>11) (Kehtetu - 12.04.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </eesti>
<inglise>11) (Repealed - 12.04.2000 entered into force 01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </inglise>
<eesti>12) (Kehtetu - 12.04.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </eesti>
<inglise>12) (Repealed - 12.04.2000 entered into force 01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </inglise>
<eesti>13) (Kehtetu - 12.04.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </eesti>
<inglise>13) (Repealed - 12.04.2000 entered into force 01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </inglise>
<eesti>14) garant - kolmas isik, kes vastavalt tollieeskirjadele v&otilde;i k&auml;esolevale seadusele on v&otilde;tnud endale kohustuse tasuda koos maksumaksjaga v&otilde;i iseseisvalt maksuv&otilde;lg summas, mille ulatuses esitati tagatis; </eesti>
<inglise>14) "guarantor" means a third person who, pursuant to customs rules or this Act, has undertaken, either with a taxpayer or independently, to pay tax arrears in an amount for which the guarantee has been provided; </inglise>
<eesti>(10.04.96 j&otilde;ust.12.05.96 - RT I 1996, 29, 577; 12.04.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </eesti>
<inglise>(10.04.96 entered into force 12.05.96 - RT I 1996, 29, 577; 12.04.2000 entered into force 01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </inglise>
<eesti>15) maksuteade - maksuhalduri poolt v&auml;ljastatud kirjalik teade tasumisele kuuluva maksusumma kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>15) "tax notice" means a written notice issued by a tax authority concerning the amount of tax due; </inglise>
<eesti>(17.02.99 j&otilde;ust.01.04.99 - RT I 1999, 27, 394) </eesti>
<inglise>(17.02.99 entered into force 01.04.99 - RT I 1999, 27, 394) </inglise>
<eesti>16) p&uuml;siv tegevuskoht - koht, mille kaudu t&auml;ielikult v&otilde;i osaliselt toimub mitteresidendi p&uuml;siv majandustegevus Eestis. </eesti>
<inglise>16) "permanent establishment" means the place through which the permanent economic activity of a non-resident is fully or partially carried out in Estonia. </inglise>
<eesti>(17.02.99 j&otilde;ust.01.04.99 - RT I 1999, 27, 394) </eesti>
<inglise>(17.02.99 entered into force 01.04.99 - RT I 1999, 27, 394) </inglise>
<eesti>(12.04.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.04.2000 entered into force 01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Maksumaksja v&otilde;i maksu kinnipidaja &otilde;igusv&otilde;ime, teov&otilde;ime ning esinduse osas juhindutakse tsiviilseadustiku &uuml;ldosa seaduse (RT I 1994, 53, 889; 65, &otilde;iend; 89, 1516; 1995, 26-28, 355; 49, 749; 87, 1540; 1996, 40, 773; 42, 811; 1998, 30, 409; 59, 941; 1999, 10, 155) vastavatest s&auml;tetest, kui k&auml;esolevast seadusest v&otilde;i maksuseadusest ei tulene teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The corresponding provisions of the General Part of the Civil Code Act (RT I 1994, 53, 889; 65, correction notice; 89, 1516; 1995, 26-28, 355; 49, 749; 87, 1540; 1996, 40, 773; 42, 811; 1998, 30, 409; 59, 941; 1999, 10, 155) shall apply to the passive legal capacity, active legal capacity and representation of taxpayers or withholding agents unless otherwise provided by this Act or a tax Act. </inglise>
<eesti>Teov&otilde;imetu v&otilde;i piiratud teov&otilde;imega isiku nimel t&auml;idab k&auml;esolevast seadusest v&otilde;i maksuseadusest tulenevaid kohustusi tema seaduslik esindaja v&otilde;i eestkostja. </eesti>
<inglise>The obligations, arising from this Act or a tax Act, of persons without active legal capacity or persons with restricted active legal capacity shall be performed in the name thereof by the legal representatives or guardians of such persons. </inglise>
<eesti>Alaealine, kellele on vastavalt tsiviilseadustiku &uuml;ldosa seaduse &sect; 10 3. l&otilde;ikes s&auml;testatule antud &otilde;igus tegeleda majandustegevusega, t&auml;idab k&auml;esolevast seadusest v&otilde;i maksuseadusest tulenevaid kohustusi iseseisvalt. </eesti>
<inglise>Minors who, pursuant to the provisions of subsection 10 (3) of the General Part of the Civil Code Act, are granted the right to engage in economic activity shall perform obligations arising from this Act or a tax Act independently. </inglise>
<eesti>Riigi- v&otilde;i kohaliku omavalitsus&uuml;ksuse asutuse &otilde;igusi ja kohustusi maksumaksjana v&otilde;i maksu kinnipidajana teostab asutuse juht vastavalt asutuse p&otilde;him&auml;&auml;ruses antud p&auml;devusele. </eesti>
<inglise>The rights and obligations of state or local government agencies as taxpayers or withholding agents shall be exercised by the heads of such agencies within the limits of the competence provided by the statutes of the agencies. </inglise>
<eesti>(12.04.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.04.2000 entered into force 01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esolevas seaduses ja maksuseaduses s&auml;testatud t&auml;htaegade ja t&auml;htp&auml;evade arvutamisel juhindutakse tsiviilseadustiku &uuml;ldosa seaduse vastavatest s&auml;tetest. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The terms and due dates provided for in this Act and in tax Acts shall be calculated pursuant to the corresponding provisions of the General Part of the Civil Code Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(12.04.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.04.2000 entered into force 01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 3. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 3. </inglise>
<eesti>Maksus&uuml;steem </eesti>
<inglise>Tax system </inglise>
<eesti>Maksus&uuml;steem koosneb maksuseadustega s&auml;testatud ja kehtestatud riiklikest maksudest ning seaduse alusel valla- v&otilde;i linnavolikogu (edaspidi volikogu) poolt oma haldusterritooriumil kehtestatavatest kohalikest maksudest. </eesti>
<inglise>The tax system consists of state taxes provided and imposed by tax Acts and local taxes imposed by a rural municipality or city council (hereinafter council) in its administrative territory pursuant to law. </inglise>
<eesti>(21.09.94 j&otilde;ust.24.10.94 - RT I 1994, 68, 1169) </eesti>
<inglise>(21.09.94 entered into force 24.10.94 - RT I 1994, 68, 1169) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 4. (Kehtetu - 17.02.99 j&otilde;ust.01.04.99 - RT I 1999, 27, 394) </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 4. (Repealed - 17.02.99 entered into force 01.04.99 - RT I 1999, 27, 394) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 5. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 5. </inglise>
<eesti>Riiklikud maksud </eesti>
<inglise>State taxes </inglise>
<eesti>Riiklikud maksud on: </eesti>
<inglise>State taxes are: </inglise>
<eesti>1) aktsiisid; </eesti>
<inglise>1) excise duties; </inglise>
<eesti>2) tulumaksud; </eesti>
<inglise>2) income taxes; </inglise>
<eesti>3) hasartm&auml;ngumaks; </eesti>
<inglise>3) gambling tax; </inglise>
<eesti>4) kinke- ja p&auml;randimaks; </eesti>
<inglise>4) gift and inheritance tax; </inglise>
<eesti>5) k&auml;ibemaks; </eesti>
<inglise>5) value added tax; </inglise>
<eesti>6) maamaks; </eesti>
<inglise>6) land tax; </inglise>
<eesti>7) sotsiaalmaks; </eesti>
<inglise>7) social tax; </inglise>
<eesti>8) tollimaks; </eesti>
<inglise>8) customs duty; </inglise>
<eesti>9) raskeveokimaks. </eesti>
<inglise>9) heavy goods vehicle tax. </inglise>
<eesti>(24.01.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2003- RT I 2001, 17, 76) </eesti>
<inglise>(24.01.2001 entered into force 01.01.2003 - RT I 2001, 17, 76) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 6. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 6. </inglise>
<eesti>Kohalikud maksud </eesti>
<inglise>Local taxes </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kohalikud maksud kehtestatakse volikogu poolt seaduse alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Local taxes are imposed by the council pursuant to law. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Volikogude poolt kehtestatavad maksud ei tohi takistada inimeste, kaupade ja teenuste vaba liikumist. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Taxes imposed by councils shall not hinder the free movement of people, goods and services. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kohalike maksude kogumist korraldab valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The collection of local taxes is organised by the rural municipality or city government. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 7. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 7. </inglise>
<eesti>Maksuseadusele esitatavad n&otilde;uded </eesti>
<inglise>Requirements for Act concerning tax </inglise>
<eesti>Maksuseaduses s&auml;testatakse: </eesti>
<inglise>The following shall be provided for in a tax Act: </inglise>
<eesti>1) maksu nimetus; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the name of the tax; </inglise>
<eesti>2) maksuobjekt; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the objects of taxation; </inglise>
<eesti>3) maksum&auml;&auml;r; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the tax rate; </inglise>
<eesti>(21.09.94 j&otilde;ust.24.10.94 - RT I 1994, 68, 1169) </eesti>
<inglise>(21.09.94 entered into force 24.10.94 - RT I 1994, 68, 1169) </inglise>
<eesti>4) maksumaksja; </eesti>
<inglise>4) the taxpayers; </inglise>
<eesti>5) maksu laekumise koht; </eesti>
<inglise>5) the place of receipt of the tax; </inglise>
<eesti>6) maksu tasumise t&auml;htp&auml;ev v&otilde;i t&auml;htaeg; </eesti>
<inglise>6) the due date or term for payment of the tax; </inglise>
<eesti>7) maksu tasumise kord; </eesti>
<inglise>7) the procedure for payment of the tax; </inglise>
<eesti>8) maksuseaduse rakendamise kord; </eesti>
<inglise>8) the procedure for implementation of the Act concerning a tax; </inglise>
<eesti>9) v&otilde;imalikud maksusoodustused ja nende tegemise kord. </eesti>
<inglise>9) possible tax incentives and the procedure for provision thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>II peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter II </inglise>
<eesti>Maksumaksja ja maksu kinnipidaja p&otilde;hi&otilde;igused ja -kohustused </eesti>
<inglise>Fundamental Rights and Duties of Taxpayers and Withholding Agents </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 8. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 8. </inglise>
<eesti>Maksude maksmise alused </eesti>
<inglise>Bases for payment of taxes </inglise>
<eesti>Maksumaksjal on kohustus maksta ainult seadustega etten&auml;htud riiklikke ja kohalikke makse maksuseadustes ning volikogu m&auml;&auml;rustes s&auml;testatud m&auml;&auml;rades ja korras. </eesti>
<inglise>Taxpayers are required to pay only such state and local taxes as are prescribed by law at the rates and pursuant to the procedure provided for in tax Acts and council regulations. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 8 (1). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 8 (1). </inglise>
<eesti>Maksukohustuse t&auml;htaegne t&auml;itmine </eesti>
<inglise>Timely satisfaction of tax liability </inglise>
<eesti>Maksumaksja on kohustatud tasuma ja maksu kinnipidaja &uuml;le kandma maksusumma maksuhalduri pangakontole seaduses etten&auml;htud t&auml;htp&auml;evaks. </eesti>
<inglise>Taxpayers are required to pay taxes and withholding agents are required to transfer taxes to the bank accounts of tax authorities by the due date prescribed by law. </inglise>
<eesti>(17.02.99 j&otilde;ust.01.04.99 - RT I 1999, 27, 394) </eesti>
<inglise>(17.02.99 entered into force 01.04.99 - RT I 1999, 27, 394) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 8 (2). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 8 (2). </inglise>
<eesti>Maksukohustuste &uuml;leminek </eesti>
<inglise>Transfer of tax liabilities </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui seadusega on ette n&auml;htud &otilde;iguste ja kohustuste &uuml;leminek &uuml;helt isikult teisele &otilde;igusj&auml;rgluse korras, siis l&auml;hevad &otilde;igusj&auml;rglasele &uuml;le ka maksuseadusest tulenevad maksukohustused ning k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 10 1. l&otilde;ikes nimetatud &otilde;igus. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If an Act prescribes the transfer of rights and obligations from one person to another pursuant to legal succession, tax liabilities arising from a tax Act and the rights specified in subsection 10 (1) of this Act also transfer to the legal successor. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) P&auml;randaja maksukohustused ning k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 10 1. l&otilde;ikes nimetatud &otilde;igus l&auml;hevad &uuml;le p&auml;rijale p&auml;rimisseaduses (RT I 1996, 38, 752; 1999, 10, 155; 88, 807; 2001, 56, 336) s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The tax liabilities and the rights specified in subsection 10 (1) of this Act belonging to a bequeather transfer to the successor pursuant to the procedure provided for in the Law of Succession Act (RT I 1996, 38, 752; 1999, 10, 155; 88, 807; 2001, 56, 336). </inglise>
<eesti>Kuni p&auml;randvara vastuv&otilde;tmiseni v&otilde;i sellest keeldumiseni t&auml;idab p&auml;randaja nimel k&auml;esolevast seadusest v&otilde;i maksuseadusest tulenevaid kohustusi p&auml;randvara hooldaja v&otilde;i testamendit&auml;itja. </eesti>
<inglise>Until acceptance of or refusal to accept an estate, the obligations arising from this Act or a tax Act shall be performed in the name of the bequeather by the administrator of the estate or the executor of the will. </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;randvara hooldaja v&otilde;i testamendit&auml;itja t&auml;idab p&auml;randaja rahalisi maksukohustusi p&auml;randvara arvel. </eesti>
<inglise>The administrator of an estate or executor of a will performs the financial tax liabilities of the bequeather from the funds of the estate. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Ettev&otilde;tte v&otilde;i selle osa omandi v&otilde;i valduse &uuml;leminekul l&auml;hevad ettev&otilde;tte v&otilde;i selle organisatsiooniliselt iseseisva osaga olemuslikult seotud maksukohustused ning k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 10 1. l&otilde;ikes nimetatud &otilde;igus &uuml;le omandajale v&otilde;i valduse saajale vastavalt &auml;riseadustiku (RT I 1995, 26-28, 355; RT I 1998, 91-93, 1500; 1999, 10, 155; 23, 355; 24, 360; 57, 596; 102, 907; 2000, 29, 172; 49, 303; 55, 365; 57, 373; 2001, 34, 185; 56, 332 ja 336; 89, 532) &sect; 5 2. ja 3. l&otilde;ikes s&auml;testatule. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Upon a transfer of ownership or possession of an enterprise or a part thereof, tax liabilities related to the enterprise or to the organisationally independent part thereof and the rights specified in subsection 10 (1) of this Act transfer to the transferee or recipient of possession pursuant to the provisions of subsections 5 (2) and (3) of the Commercial Code (RT I 1995, 26-28, 355; 1998, 91-93, 1500; 1999, 10, 155; 23, 355; 24, 360; 57, 596; 102, 907; 2000, 29, 172; 49, 303; 55, 365; 57, 373; 57, 373; 2001, 34, 185; 56, 332 and 336; 89, 532). </inglise>
<eesti>(12.04.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.04.2000 entered into force 01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 9. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 9. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;igus saada teavet maksude kohta </eesti>
<inglise>Right to obtain information concerning taxes </inglise>
<eesti>Maksumaksjal ja maksu kinnipidajal on &otilde;igus saada maksuhaldurilt teavet nende poolt maksmisele ja kinnipidamisele kuuluvate maksude, samuti maksusumma m&auml;&auml;ramise aluste ning arvutamise korra kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>Taxpayers and withholding agents have the right to obtain information from tax authorities concerning the taxes to be paid or withheld by them, the bases for assessment of amounts of tax and the procedure for calculation thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>(10.04.96 j&otilde;ust.12.05.96 - RT I 1996, 29, 577) </eesti>
<inglise>(10.04.96 entered into force 12.05.96 - RT I 1996, 29, 577) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 9 (1). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 9 (1). </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;igus esindajale </eesti>
<inglise>Right to representation </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Maksumaksjal v&otilde;i maksu kinnipidajal on &otilde;igus esindajale. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Taxpayers and withholding agents have the right to representation. </inglise>
<eesti>Esindaja v&otilde;ib maksumaksja v&otilde;i maksu kinnipidaja nimel osaleda k&otilde;igis menetlustoimingutes, v&auml;lja arvatud juhul, kui seadusest v&otilde;i toimingu olemusest tulenevalt on n&otilde;utav maksumaksja v&otilde;i maksu kinnipidaja isiklik osav&otilde;tt. </eesti>
<inglise>A representative may participate, in the name of a taxpayer or withholding agent, in all procedural acts, unless the personal participation of the taxpayer or withholding agent is required pursuant to law or due to the nature of the act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Esindaja peab maksuhalduri n&otilde;udmisel esitama esindust t&otilde;endava volikirja. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A representative shall submit an authorisation document certifying representation at the request of the tax authority. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Esindajal on maksumaksja v&otilde;i maksu kinnipidaja esindamisel esindatava &otilde;igused ja kohustused, v&auml;lja arvatud &otilde;igus enammakstud maksusumma tagasisaamisele, ning kohustused, mis oma olemusest tingituna tuleb t&auml;ita maksumaksja v&otilde;i maksu kinnipidaja poolt isiklikult. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Upon representing a taxpayer or withholding agent, a representative has the rights and obligations of the person represented, except the right to a tax refund and obligations which, by their nature, must be performed by the taxpayer or withholding agent personally. </inglise>
<eesti>(12.04.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.04.2000 entered into force 01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 10. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 10. </inglise>
<eesti>Enammakstud maksusumma tagasisaamise &otilde;igus </eesti>
<inglise>Right to tax refund </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Maksumaksjal, kes on tasunud maksu etten&auml;htust enam, on &otilde;igus kolme aasta jooksul maksu tasumise t&auml;htp&auml;evast arvates taotleda maksuhaldurilt enammakstud maksusumma: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A taxpayer who has paid more than the prescribed tax has the right to apply to the tax authority within three years after the due date for payment of the tax for: </inglise>
<eesti>1) tagastamist; </eesti>
<inglise>1) a refund of the overpaid amount of tax; </inglise>
<eesti>2) tasaarvestamist maksumaksja poolt tasumisele kuuluva ja sama maksuhalduri poolt hallatava riikliku maksu summaga; </eesti>
<inglise>2) offsetting of the amount to be paid by the taxpayer and the amount of a state tax administrated by the same tax authority; </inglise>
<eesti>3) tasaarvestamist sama maksuhalduri poolt k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 30 v&otilde;i haldus&otilde;iguserikkumiste seadustiku (RT 1992, 29, 396; RT I 2001, 74, 453) alusel maksumaksjale m&auml;&auml;ratud rahatrahvide ning k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 28 alusel maksumaksjale arvestatud intresside v&otilde;lgnevusega. </eesti>
<inglise>3) offsetting of fines imposed on the taxpayer by the same tax authority on the basis of &sect; 30 of this Act or on the basis of the Code of Administrative Offences (RT 1992, 29, 396; RT I 2001, 74, 453) and interest arrears calculated for the taxpayer on the basis of &sect; 28 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(12.04.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.04.2000 entered into force 01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Maksudeklaratsioonis sisalduva v&otilde;i maksumaksja poolt eraldi esitatud kirjaliku taotluse alusel tagastab maksuhaldur maksumaksja poolt enammakstud maksusumma v&otilde;i arvestab selle k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ike punktides 2 v&otilde;i 3 nimetatud rahaliste kohustuste katteks 30 kalendrip&auml;eva jooksul, arvates taotluse saamise p&auml;evale j&auml;rgnevast p&auml;evast, v&auml;lja arvatud k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 3. ja 4. l&otilde;ikes s&auml;testatud juhtudel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A tax authority shall, on the basis of a written application included in a tax return or submitted separately by a taxpayer, refund the overpaid tax or calculate the overpaid amount of tax to be used to set off financial obligations specified in clauses (1) 2) or 3) of this section within thirty calendar days as of the date following the date of receipt of the application, except in the cases provided for in subsections (3) and (4) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui taotlus esitatakse enne maksu tasumise t&auml;htp&auml;eva, tagastatakse v&otilde;i tasaarvestatakse maksusumma 30 kalendrip&auml;eva jooksul tasumise t&auml;htp&auml;evale j&auml;rgnevast p&auml;evast arvates. </eesti>
<inglise>If an application is submitted prior to the due date for payment of the tax, the tax shall be refunded or the amount shall be calculated as a set off within thirty calendar days as of the date following the due date for payment. </inglise>
<eesti>(12.04.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.04.2000 entered into force 01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Riiklike maksude maksuhalduril on &otilde;igus kirjaliku otsusega j&auml;tta enammakstud maksusumma tagastamise taotlus rahuldamata ja ilma maksumaksja taotluseta tasaarvestada enammakstud maksusumma: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The tax authorities for state taxes have the right to deny an application for a refund of overpaid tax by a written decision and to use the overpaid amount of tax as set off without an application from the taxpayer: </inglise>
<eesti>1) sama maksuhalduri poolt hallatavate riiklike maksude v&otilde;i k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 28 alusel arvestatud intresside v&otilde;lgnevustega, kui maksusumma tasumise t&auml;htp&auml;ev on saabunud v&otilde;i saabub enne enammakstud maksusumma tagastamise t&auml;htp&auml;eva saabumist, v&otilde;i </eesti>
<inglise>1) to cover arrears of state taxes administered by the same tax authority or interest arrears calculated on the basis of &sect; 28 of this Act if the due date for payment of the amount has arrived or arrives prior to the date for refund of the overpaid tax, or </inglise>
<eesti>2) k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 30 v&otilde;i haldus&otilde;iguserikkumiste seadustiku alusel sama maksuhalduri poolt m&auml;&auml;ratud rahatrahvide v&otilde;lgnevustega, kui maksumaksja v&otilde;i maksu kinnipidaja pole trahvi tasunud 15 kalendrip&auml;eva jooksul p&auml;rast trahviotsuse k&auml;tteandmist v&otilde;i trahviotsuse vaidlustamise korral 15 kalendrip&auml;eva jooksul, arvates temale kaebuse rahuldamata j&auml;tmisest teatamise p&auml;evale j&auml;rgnevast p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>2) to cover arrears of fines imposed by the same tax authority on the basis of &sect; 30 of this Act or on the basis of the Code of Administrative Offences, if the taxpayer or withholding agent has not paid the fine within fifteen calendar days after service of a decision imposing the fine or, in the case of contestation of the decision imposing the fine, within fifteen calendar days as of the date following the date on which the taxpayer or withholding agent is informed of the appeal being dismissed. </inglise>
<eesti>(12.04.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.04.2000 entered into force 01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Riiklike maksude maksuhalduril on &otilde;igus maksumaksja tegevuses maksukorralduse seaduse v&otilde;i maksuseaduste rikkumise tunnuste tuvastamisel v&otilde;i maksuhalduri poolt maksuseaduse rikkumise fakti kohta kriminaalasja algatamiseks avalduse esitamisel peatada enammakstud maksusumma tagastamine: </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The tax authorities for state taxes have the right to suspend the refund of overpaid taxes upon the ascertainment of evidence of a violation of the Taxation Act or a tax Act in the activities of the taxpayer or upon the submission by a tax authority of a petition to commence criminal proceedings regarding the violation of a tax Act: </inglise>
<eesti>(12.04.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.04.2000 entered into force 01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </inglise>
<eesti>1) otsuse j&otilde;ustumiseni haldus&otilde;iguserikkumise asjas, v&auml;lja arvatud k&auml;esoleva l&otilde;ike punktis 2 s&auml;testatud juhul; </eesti>
<inglise>1) until the entry into force of a judgment in an administrative offence matter, with the exception of the cases provided for in clause 2) of this subsection; </inglise>
<eesti>2) haldus&otilde;iguserikkumiste seadustiku (RT 1992, 29, 396; RT I 2001, 74, 453) paragrahv 226 alusel uurimisorganile &uuml;leantud materjalide alusel algatatud kriminaalasjas kohtuotsuse j&otilde;ustumiseni v&otilde;i kriminaalasja algatamisest keeldumise v&otilde;i l&otilde;petamise m&auml;&auml;ruse tegemiseni; </eesti>
<inglise>2) until the entry into force of a court judgment in a criminal proceeding commenced on the basis of material transferred to an investigative body pursuant to &sect; 226 of the Code of Administrative Offences (RT 1992, 29, 396; RT I 2001, 74, 453) or until the issue of a ruling on refusal to commence a criminal proceeding or on termination of a criminal proceeding; </inglise>
<eesti>(17.02.99 j&otilde;ust.01.04.99 - RT I 1999, 27, 394) </eesti>
<inglise>(17.02.99 entered into force 01.04.99 - RT I 1999, 27, 394) </inglise>
<eesti>3) kriminaalasjas kohtuotsuse j&otilde;ustumiseni v&otilde;i kriminaalasja algatamisest keeldumise v&otilde;i l&otilde;petamise m&auml;&auml;ruse tegemiseni, v&auml;lja arvatud k&auml;esoleva l&otilde;ike punktis 4 s&auml;testatud juhul; </eesti>
<inglise>3) until the entry into force of a court judgment in a criminal proceeding or until the issue of a ruling on refusal to commence a criminal proceeding or on termination of a criminal proceeding, with the exception of the case provided for in clause 4) of this subsection; </inglise>
<eesti>(17.02.99 j&otilde;ust.01.04.99 - RT I 1999, 27, 394) </eesti>
<inglise>(17.02.99 entered into force 01.04.99 - RT I 1999, 27, 394) </inglise>
<eesti>4) vastavalt kriminaalmenetluse koodeksi (ENSV &Uuml;lemn&otilde;ukogu Teataja 1961, 1, 4 ja lisa; RT I 1995, 6-8, 69; 15, 173; 83, 1441; 1996, 6, 101; 31, 631; 48, 943) paragrahv 96 4. l&otilde;ikele edasisuunatud materjalide alusel tehtud halduskaristuse otsuse j&otilde;ustumiseni v&otilde;i asja menetluse l&otilde;petamise otsuse j&otilde;ustumiseni. </eesti>
<inglise>4) until the entry into force of a judgment imposing an administrative penalty on the basis of material forwarded pursuant to subsection 96 (4) of the Code of Criminal Procedure (ENSV &Uuml;lemn&otilde;ukogu Teataja (2) 1961, 1, 4 and lisa (3); RT I 1995, 6-8, 69; 15, 173; 83, 1441; 1996, 6, 101; 31, 631; 48, 943) or until the entry into force of a judgment to terminate the proceeding in a matter. </inglise>
<eesti>(07.11.96 j&otilde;ust.08.12.96 - RT I 1996, 81, 1447) </eesti>
<inglise>(07.11.96 entered into force 08.12.96 - RT I 1996, 81, 1447) </inglise>
<eesti>(5) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 4. l&otilde;ikes nimetatud juhul teeb maksuhaldur kirjaliku otsuse, milles m&auml;rgitakse enammakstud maksusumma, mille tagastamine peatatakse, ning peatamise tinginud asjaolud koos viidetega vastavatele seaduss&auml;tetele. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) In the case specified in subsection (4) of this section, the tax authority shall make a written decision in which the overpaid amount of tax, the refund of which is suspended, and the circumstances which cause the suspension together with references to the relevant provisions of Acts are indicated. </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ike punktides 2 ja 3 nimetatud taotluse lahendamisel ning 3. l&otilde;ikes nimetatud juhtudel teeb maksuhaldur kirjaliku otsuse viitega 1. v&otilde;i 3. l&otilde;ike vastavale punktile, mille alusel enammakstud maksusumma arvestatakse maksumaksja muude rahaliste kohustuste katteks. </eesti>
<inglise>Upon adjudication of applications specified in clauses (1) 2) and 3) of this section and in the cases specified in subsection (3) of this section, the tax authority shall make a written decision with a reference to the corresponding clause of subsection (1) or (3) on the basis of which the overpaid amount of tax shall be calculated to cover other financial obligations of the taxpayer. </inglise>
<eesti>Otsus antakse maksumaksjale k&auml;tte allkirja vastu v&otilde;i saadetakse posti teel. </eesti>
<inglise>The decision shall be delivered to the taxpayer against a signature or forwarded by post. </inglise>
<eesti>(12.04.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.04.2000 entered into force 01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Enammakstud maksusumma tagastamise korral maksumaksjale selle &uuml;lekandmise teel tema v&auml;lisriigis olevale pangakontole kannab tagastatava summa &uuml;lekandmise kulud maksumaksja. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) Upon the refund of overpaid tax to a taxpayer by transferring the amount to the taxpayer's bank account located in a foreign state, the costs of transferring the refunded amount shall be covered by the taxpayer. </inglise>
<eesti>(12.04.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.04.2000 entered into force 01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 11. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 11. </inglise>
<eesti>Maksusaladuse kaitse </eesti>
<inglise>Confidentiality protection </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Maksuhalduri ametnikud ja teenistujad on kohustatud hoidma saladuses maksumaksjat v&otilde;i maksu kinnipidajat puudutavat informatsiooni, sealhulgas &auml;ri- ja pangasaladust, mida nad on teada saanud maksude tasumise &otilde;igsuse kontrollimise, tasumisele kuuluva maksusumma m&auml;&auml;ramise, maksuv&otilde;lgade sissen&otilde;udmise, maksuseaduste rikkumise asja menetlemise v&otilde;i muude teenistuskohustuste t&auml;itmise k&auml;igus. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Officials and employees of tax authorities are required to maintain the confidentiality of information concerning taxpayers or withholding agents, including business secrets and information subject to banking secrecy, obtained by such officials and employees in the course of verification of the correctness of taxes paid, assessment of an amount of tax to be paid, collection of tax arrears, conducting of proceedings concerning violations of a tax Act or the performance of other duties. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ikes nimetatud informatsiooni on lubatud avaldada ainult maksumaksja v&otilde;i maksu kinnipidaja kirjalikul n&otilde;usolekul v&otilde;i k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 3.-5. l&otilde;ikes nimetatud juhtudel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Information specified in subsection (1) of this section may be disclosed only with the written consent of the taxpayer or withholding agent or in the cases specified in subsections (3) -(5) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Maksumaksja v&otilde;i maksu kinnipidaja n&otilde;usolekuta, kuid teda informeerides, v&otilde;ib maksuhaldur anda tema kohta informatsiooni: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A tax authority may provide information about a taxpayer or withholding agent, having informed the taxpayer or withholding agent thereof, without the taxpayer's or withholding agent's consent to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) Riigikontrollile tema &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the State Audit Office for the performance of its duties; </inglise>
<eesti>2) v&auml;lisriigi p&auml;devatele organitele selle riigi residendist maksumaksja kohta vastavalt v&auml;lislepingus s&auml;testatud tingimustele; </eesti>
<inglise>2) competent bodies of a foreign state concerning a resident taxpayer in such state under the conditions provided for in an international agreement; </inglise>
<eesti>3) Euroopa &Uuml;henduste ja selle liikmesriikide organitele, kes on p&auml;devad maksumaksjaga v&otilde;i maksu kinnipidajaga seotud informatsiooni vahetamiseks v&auml;lislepingus v&otilde;i Euroopa &Uuml;henduste &otilde;igusaktides etten&auml;htud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>3) bodies of the European Communities and Member States thereof who are competent to exchange information related to taxpayers or withholding agents pursuant to the procedure prescribed in an international agreement or legislation of the European Communities. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Maksumaksja v&otilde;i maksu kinnipidaja n&otilde;usolekuta ja teda informeerimata v&otilde;ib maksuhaldur avaldada: </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Without the consent of or without having informed a taxpayer or withholding agent, a tax authority may disclose: </inglise>
<eesti>1) maksumaksja v&otilde;i maksu kinnipidaja maksuv&otilde;la suurust; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the amount of tax arrears of the taxpayer or withholding agent; </inglise>
<eesti>2) kohtulahendit v&otilde;i k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 35 kohaselt esitatud kaebuse v&otilde;i vastulause lahendamisel tehtud otsuse resolutiivosa, mille peale kohtusse kaebuse esitamise t&auml;htaeg on kaebust esitamata m&ouml;&ouml;da lastud; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the decision or the conclusion of a judgment made upon adjudication of an appeal or objection filed pursuant to &sect; 35 of this Act, against which an appeal has not been filed during the term for filing an appeal with a court; </inglise>
<eesti>3) k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 11 (4) kohaselt Maksuameti kohalikus asutuses registreeritud juriidilise isiku v&otilde;i asutuse v&otilde;i f&uuml;&uuml;silisest isikust ettev&otilde;tja v&otilde;i v&auml;lismaa juriidilise isiku p&uuml;siva tegevuskoha registrisse kandmise ja registrist kustutamise kuup&auml;eva, samuti nimetatud isiku v&otilde;i asutuse registreerimisel v&auml;ljastatud t&otilde;endi numbrit ning nimetatud t&otilde;endile kantud andmeid; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the date on which the permanent establishment of a legal person or agency or sole proprietor registered with a local office of the Tax Board pursuant to &sect; 11 (4) of this Act, or a foreign legal person is entered in or deleted from the register, and the number of the certificate issued upon registration of the specified person or agency and the information entered on the specified certificate; </inglise>
<eesti>4) maksumaksja k&auml;ibemaksukohustuslasena registrisse kandmise ja registrist kustutamise kuup&auml;eva ning tema k&auml;ibemaksukohustuslasena registreerimise numbrit; </eesti>
<inglise>4) the date of entry of the taxpayer in the register as a payer of value added tax and the date of deletion of the taxpayer from the register and the number of registration of the taxpayer as a payer of value added tax; </inglise>
<eesti>5) valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsusele selle f&uuml;&uuml;silise isiku nime, isikukoodi, maksustatava tulu suuruse enne ja p&auml;rast seadusega lubatud mahaarvamisi, samuti maksustatavalt tulult arvestatud tulumaksusumma suuruse, kelle tulumaksust kantakse seadusega s&auml;testatud osa vastava omavalitsus&uuml;ksuse eelarvesse; </eesti>
<inglise>5) the names, personal identification codes, taxable income, before and after the deductions permitted by law, and amount of income tax calculated on taxable income of natural persons from whose income tax a part provided by law is transferred to the budget of a local government, to the rural municipality and city government; </inglise>
<eesti>(02.05.2001 j&otilde;ust.02.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 48, 266) </eesti>
<inglise>(02.05.2001 entered into force 02.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 48, 266) </inglise>
<eesti>6) valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsusele tema haldusterritooriumil asuva maksu kinnipidaja poolt valla v&otilde;i linna kasuks maksuhaldurile &uuml;lekantud maksusumma; </eesti>
<inglise>6) the amount of tax transferred to the tax authority for the benefit of a rural municipality or city by the withholding agent located within the administrative territory of the rural municipality or city government, to the rural municipality or city government; </inglise>
<eesti>7) sotsiaalkindlustusega tegelevatele riigiasutustele seadusega etten&auml;htud andmeid; </eesti>
<inglise>7) the information prescribed by law to state agencies engaged in social insurance; </inglise>
<eesti>8) informatsiooni &auml;riregistri pidajale registrikartoteegi andmete osas; </eesti>
<inglise>8) information relating to the card register to the registrar of the commercial register; </inglise>
<eesti>9) Statistikaametile ja Riigihangete Ametile talle seadusega pandud &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmiseks vajalikku informatsiooni; </eesti>
<inglise>9) information to the Statistical Office and Public Procurement Office which is necessary for the performance of functions imposed on the Statistical Office by law; </inglise>
<eesti>(19.10.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 84, 534) </eesti>
<inglise>(19.10.2000 entered into force 01.04.2000 - RT I 2000, 84, 534) </inglise>
<eesti>10) rahandusministrile andmeid, mis on seotud maksumaksjale v&otilde;i maksu kinnipidajale antud riigiabiga konkurentsiseaduse (RT I 1998, 30, 410; 1999, 89, 813) &sect; 19 t&auml;henduses; </eesti>
<inglise>10) information to the Minister of Finance concerning state aid within the meaning of the Competition Act (RT I 1998, 30, 410; 1999, 89, 813) granted to the taxpayer or withholding agent; </inglise>
<eesti>11) teisele riiklike maksude maksuhaldurile k&otilde;iki maksumaksja v&otilde;i maksu kinnipidaja kohta k&auml;ivaid andmeid; </eesti>
<inglise>11) any information concerning the taxpayer or withholding agent to other tax authorities of state taxes; </inglise>
<eesti>12) kohtut&auml;iturile t&auml;itetoimingute sooritamiseks vajalikke andmeid; </eesti>
<inglise>12) information to bailiffs necessary for the performance of enforcement actions; </inglise>
<eesti>13) rahapesu andmeb&uuml;roole rahapesu v&otilde;i sellega seotud kuritegude v&auml;ltimiseks, avastamiseks ja uurimiseks vajalikke andmeid. </eesti>
<inglise>13) information to the Financial Intelligence Unit necessary for the prevention, detection and investigation of money laundering or criminal offences related to money laundering. </inglise>
<eesti>(18.10.2000 j&otilde;ust.17.11.2000 - RT I 2000, 84, 533) </eesti>
<inglise>(18.10.2000 entered into force 17.11.2000 - RT I 2000, 84, 533) </inglise>
<eesti>14) valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsusele mootors&otilde;idukimaksu haldamiseks vajalikku informatsiooni raskeveokimaksuga maksustatavate mootors&otilde;idukite kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>14) information to rural municipality governments or city governments concerning motor vehicles subject to heavy goods vehicle tax which is necessary for the administration of motor vehicle taxes; </inglise>
<eesti>(24.01.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2003 - RT I 2001, 17, 76) </eesti>
<inglise>(24.01.2001 entered into force 01.01.2003 - RT I 2001, 17, 76) </inglise>
<eesti>15) &otilde;iguste valdajale andmeid intellektuaalset omandit rikkuva kauba sisse- ja v&auml;ljaveo t&otilde;kestamise seaduses etten&auml;htud juhtudel. </eesti>
<inglise>15) information on holders of rights in the cases prescribed in the Act on Prevention of Importation and Exportation of Goods Infringing Intellectual Property Rights. </inglise>
<eesti>(06.06.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.09.2001 - RT I 2001, 56, 335) </eesti>
<inglise>(06.06.2001 entered into force 01.09.2001 - RT I 2001, 56, 335) </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Maksuhaldur v&otilde;ib maksumaksja n&otilde;usoleku ja teadmiseta anda kohtule v&otilde;i muule p&auml;devale riigiasutusele teavet kriminaal-, tsiviil- v&otilde;i haldus&otilde;iguserikkumise asja uurimiseks, menetlemiseks, arutamiseks ning karistuse m&auml;&auml;ramiseks vajalike andmete kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The tax authority may provide information which is necessary for the investigation, hearing and consideration of a matter subject to a criminal, civil or administrative proceeding and for imposition of punishment to a court or to another competent state agency without the consent or knowledge of a taxpayer. </inglise>
<eesti>(14.06.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.10.2001 - RT I 2001, 65, 378) </eesti>
<inglise>(14.06.2001 entered into force 01.10.2001 - RT I 2001, 65, 378) </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Kui seaduses ei ole s&auml;testatud teisiti, on k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 3.-5. l&otilde;ike alusel informatsiooni saanud asutuste ametnikud ja teenistujad kohustatud hoidma saladuses nimetatud l&otilde;igete alusel neile edastatud informatsiooni maksumaksja ja maksu kinnipidaja kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) Unless otherwise provided by law, officials and employees of agencies who obtain information on the basis of subsections (3) -(5) of this section are required to maintain the confidentiality of information concerning taxpayers or withholding agents which is forwarded to such officials and employees on the basis of the specified subsections. </inglise>
