<eesti>Maksuhaldur </eesti>
<inglise>Tax authorities </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Riiklike maksude maksuhaldurid on Tolliamet ning Maksuamet ja tema kohalikud asutused. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The tax authorities for state taxes are the Customs Board, and the Tax Board and its local offices. </inglise>
<eesti>Kohalike maksude maksuhaldurid oma haldusterritooriumil on valla- ja linnavalitsused ning vastavalt kohalike maksude seaduse paragrahvi 3 3. l&otilde;ikele Maksuameti kohalikud asutused. </eesti>
<inglise>The tax authorities for local taxes are the rural municipality and city governments within their administrative territories, and local offices of the Tax Board pursuant to subsection 3 (3) of the Local Taxes Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(21.09.94 j&otilde;ust.24.10.94 - RT I 1994, 68, 1169; 12.04.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </eesti>
<inglise>(21.09.94 entered into force 24.10.94 - RT I 1994, 68, 1169; 12.04.2000 entered into force 01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Maksuhaldur on kohustatud kontrollima maksude tasumise &otilde;igsust, m&auml;&auml;rama seaduses s&auml;testatud juhtudel tasumisele kuuluvad maksusummad ja intressid, n&otilde;udma sisse maksuv&otilde;lad ning rakendama sanktsioone maksuseaduste rikkujate suhtes. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Tax authorities are required to verify the correctness of tax payments, assess amounts of tax and interest due in the cases provided by law, collect tax arrears and implement sanctions against persons who violate tax Acts. </inglise>
<eesti>(10.04.96 j&otilde;ust.12.05.96 - RT I 1996, 29, 577) </eesti>
<inglise>(10.04.96 entered into force 12.05.96 - RT I 1996, 29, 577) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 15. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 15. </inglise>
<eesti>Maksuhalduri ettekirjutus </eesti>
<inglise>Precept of tax authority </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Maksuhalduri keskasutuse peadirektoril, tema aset&auml;itjal, maksuhalduri kohaliku asutuse direktoril, tema aset&auml;itjal ja nende poolt volitatud ametnikel on &otilde;igus teha maksumaksjale, maksu kinnipidajale v&otilde;i kolmandale isikule maksuseaduste ja k&auml;esoleva seaduse alusel t&auml;itmiseks kohustuslikke ettekirjutusi, milles peab sisalduma: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The director general of the central tax authority and the deputy director general, the directors of local offices of tax authorities and the deputy directors, and officials authorised thereby have the right to issue mandatory precepts pursuant to tax Acts and this Act to taxpayers, withholding agents and third persons, which shall set out: </inglise>
<eesti>1) maksuhalduri nimetus ja aadress; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the name and address of the tax authority; </inglise>
<eesti>(17.02.99 j&otilde;ust.01.04.99 - RT I 1999, 27, 394) </eesti>
<inglise>(17.02.99 entered into force 01.04.99 - RT I 1999, 27, 394) </inglise>
<eesti>2) ettekirjutuse koostanud ametniku nimi ja ametikoht; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the name and position of the official who prepared the precept; </inglise>
<eesti>3) ettekirjutuse tegemise kuup&auml;ev; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the date of preparation of the precept; </inglise>
<eesti>4) maksumaksja, maksu kinnipidaja v&otilde;i kolmanda isiku nimi ja aadress; </eesti>
<inglise>4) the name and address of the taxpayer, withholding agent or third person; </inglise>
<eesti>5) ettekirjutuse tegemist tingivad asjaolud koos viidetega vastavate seaduste s&auml;tetele; </eesti>
<inglise>5) the circumstances due to which the precept is issued with references to the provisions of the corresponding Acts; </inglise>
<eesti>6) ettekirjutuse t&auml;itmise t&auml;htaeg; </eesti>
<inglise>6) the term for compliance with the precept; </inglise>
<eesti>7) ettekirjutuse t&auml;itmata j&auml;tmisel rakendatavad sanktsioonid. </eesti>
<inglise>7) the sanctions to be imposed upon failure to comply with the precept. </inglise>
<eesti>(10.04.96 j&otilde;ust.12.05.96 - RT I 1996, 29, 577) </eesti>
<inglise>(10.04.96 entered into force 12.05.96 - RT I 1996, 29, 577) </inglise>
<eesti>(17.02.99 j&otilde;ust.01.04.99 - RT I 1999, 27, 394) </eesti>
<inglise>(17.02.99 entered into force 01.04.99 - RT I 1999, 27, 394) </inglise>
<eesti>8) ettekirjutuse vaidlustamise kord ja t&auml;htaeg. </eesti>
<inglise>8) the procedure and term for contesting the precept. </inglise>
<eesti>(12.04.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.04.2000 entered into force 01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Ettekirjutus antakse ettekirjutuse adressaadile v&otilde;i tema esindajale &uuml;le k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 15 (1) s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A precept shall be delivered to the addressee indicated in the precept or a representative of the addressee pursuant to the procedure provided for in &sect; 15 (1) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>Maksumaksjale v&otilde;i maksu kinnipidajale, kelle maksuv&otilde;la, maksukohustuse m&auml;&auml;ramise v&otilde;i maksukohustuse t&auml;itmise &otilde;igsuse kontrollimisega seonduvalt tehti kolmandale isikule ettekirjutus k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 20 1. l&otilde;ike, &sect; 23 2. v&otilde;i 3. l&otilde;ike v&otilde;i &sect; 24 1. l&otilde;ike alusel, saadetakse k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 15 (1) s&auml;testatud korras eelnimetatud ettekirjutuse &auml;rakiri. </eesti>
<inglise>If a precept is issued to a third person on the basis of subsections 20 (1), 23 (2) or (3) or 24 (1) of this Act in connection with the tax arrears of a taxpayer or withholding agent, determination of the tax liability thereof or verification of the correctness of satisfaction of the tax liability thereof, the taxpayer or withholding agent shall receive a copy of the aforementioned precept. </inglise>
<eesti>(12.04.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.04.2000 entered into force 01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) (Kehtetu - 17.02.99 j&otilde;ust.01.04.99 - RT I 1999, 27, 394) </eesti>
<inglise>(3) (Repealed - 17.02.99 entered into force 01.04.99 - RT I 1999, 27, 394) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 15 (1). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 15 (1). </inglise>
<eesti>Ettekirjutuse &uuml;leandmine </eesti>
<inglise>Delivery of precept </inglise>
<eesti>(1) F&uuml;&uuml;silisele isikule antakse ettekirjutus &uuml;le allkirja vastu dateeritult v&otilde;i saadetakse posti teel v&auml;ljastusteatega tema elukoha aadressil v&otilde;i tema poolt maksuhaldurile teatatud postiaadressil. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A precept shall be delivered to a natural person against a signature and shall be dated, or shall be sent by post with advice of delivery to his or her residential address or the postal address of which he or she has informed the tax authority. </inglise>
<eesti>Ettekirjutus loetakse f&uuml;&uuml;silisele isikule &uuml;leantuks, kui ettekirjutuse k&auml;ttesaamise kohta on saadud ettekirjutuse adressaadi, tema esindaja v&otilde;i ettekirjutuse adressaadiga koos elava v&auml;hemalt 10-aastase isiku allkiri. </eesti>
<inglise>A precept is deemed to be delivered to the natural person if the signature of the addressee of the precept, the signature of the representative of the addressee or the signature of a person of at least 10 years of age residing with the addressee has been obtained regarding receipt of the precept. </inglise>
<eesti>(12.04.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.04.2000 entered into force 01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Juriidilisele isikule posti teel saadetud ettekirjutus loetakse &uuml;leantuks, kui ettekirjutuse saatmisest selle isiku v&otilde;i asutuse registrisse kantud aadressil on m&ouml;&ouml;dunud viis kalendrip&auml;eva Eesti piires saatmise korral v&otilde;i 30 kalendrip&auml;eva v&auml;lisriiki saatmise korral. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A precept sent to a legal person by post is deemed to be delivered: in case of delivery made within Estonia, after five calendar days have passed the sending of the precept at the address of the person or agency which is entered in the register, and in case of delivery to a foreign state, after 30 calendar days. </inglise>
<eesti>Isikule v&otilde;i asutusele, keda ei ole kantud registrisse, saadetakse ettekirjutus tema poolt maksuhaldurile teatatud aadressil. </eesti>
<inglise>Persons or agencies who are not entered in the register shall receive a precept at the address of which they have informed the tax authority. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui ettekirjutuse adressaat, tema esindaja v&otilde;i ettekirjutuse adressaadiga koos elav v&auml;hemalt 10-aastane isik keeldub ettekirjutust vastu v&otilde;tmast, teeb selle k&auml;ttetoimetaja ettekirjutusele sellekohase m&auml;rkuse ja kinnitab seda oma allkirjaga. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If the addressee of a precept, the representative of the addressee or a person of at least 10 years of age residing with the addressee refuses to receive the precept, the person delivering the precept shall make a corresponding notation on the precept and shall sign it. </inglise>
<eesti>M&auml;rkusega ettekirjutus tagastatakse maksuhaldurile ning ettekirjutus loetakse ettekirjutuse adressaadile &uuml;leantuks. </eesti>
<inglise>The precept with a notice is returned to the tax authority and it is deemed to be delivered to the addressee. </inglise>
<eesti>(12.04.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.04.2000 entered into force 01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kui ettekirjutuse adressaat ei asu v&otilde;i ei ela registrisse kantud aadressil ning maksuhalduril ei &otilde;nnestu tema elu- v&otilde;i asukohta kindlaks teha, on maksuhalduril &otilde;igus avaldada ametlikus v&auml;ljaandes Ametlikud Teadaanded teade ettekirjutuse tegemise kohta, milles sisaldub ettekirjutuse teinud maksuhalduri nimi ja postiaadress, ettekirjutuse adressaadi nimi ja registrisse kantud aadress, ettekirjutuse tegemise kuup&auml;ev ning koht, kus on v&otilde;imalik ettekirjutuse sisuga tutvuda. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If the addressee of a precept is not or does not reside at the address entered in the register and the tax authority is unable to establish the addressee's residence or location, the tax authority has the right to publish a notice on the issue of a precept in the official publication Ametlikud Teadaanded (4); the notice shall include the name and postal address of the tax authority which issued the precept, the name of the addressee and the addressee's address entered in the register, the date of issue of the precept and place in which the contents of the precept can be viewed. </inglise>
<eesti>Selliselt avaldatud ettekirjutus loetakse &uuml;leantuks teate avaldamise p&auml;evale j&auml;rgneval p&auml;eval. </eesti>
<inglise>A precept which is published in such manner is deemed to be delivered on the day following the date of publication of the notice. </inglise>
<eesti>(17.11.1999 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 92, 826; 12.04.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216; 20.06.2000 j&otilde;ust.12.07.2000 - RT I 2000, 55, 365) </eesti>
<inglise>(17.11.1999 entered into force 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 92, 826; 12.04.2000 entered into force 01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216; 20.06.2000 entered into force 12.07.2000 - RT I 2000, 55, 365) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 16. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 16. </inglise>
<eesti>Maksumaksja v&otilde;i maksu kinnipidaja territooriumi, hoonete, ruumide ja mootors&otilde;idukite kontrollimine </eesti>
<inglise>Inspection of territory, buildings, rooms and motor vehicles of taxpayer or withholding agent </inglise>
<eesti>(23.09.97 j&otilde;ust.01.01.98 - RT I 1997, 73, 1201; 17.02.99 j&otilde;ust.01.04.99 - RT I 1999, 27, 394) </eesti>
<inglise>(23.09.97 entered into force 01.01.98 - RT I 1997, 73, 1201; 17.02.99 entered into force 01.04.99 - RT I 1999, 27, 394) </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Maksukuritegude t&otilde;kestamiseks on maksuhalduri ametnikul maksuhalduri keskasutuse peadirektori v&otilde;i kohaliku asutuse direktori poolt allkirjastatud ettekirjutuse alusel ja ametit&otilde;endi etten&auml;itamisel ilma eelneva hoiatuse v&otilde;i eriloata &otilde;igus kontrollida maksumaksja v&otilde;i maksu kinnipidaja tegevuskohta. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In order to prevent tax crimes, officials of tax authorities have the right, on the basis of a precept signed by the director general of the central tax authority or the director of a local office of the tax authority and upon presentation of identification, to inspect the place of business of a taxpayer or withholding agent without prior warning or special permission. </inglise>
<eesti>(12.04.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.04.2000 entered into force 01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </inglise>
<eesti>(1 (1)) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ikes nimetatud ettekirjutus peab sisaldama k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 15 1. l&otilde;ikes loetletud andmeid ning andmeid selle kohta, millise kuriteo ettevalmistamises, katses v&otilde;i toimepanemises maksumaksjat, maksu kinnipidajat, temaga seotud v&otilde;i teda esindavat isikut kahtlustatakse, koos viidetega kriminaalkoodeksi vastavatele s&auml;tetele. </eesti>
<inglise>(1 (1)) A precept specified in subsection (1) of this section shall contain the information listed in subsection 15 (1) of this Act and information concerning the criminal offence which a taxpayer, withholding agent, or person connected with or representing the taxpayer or withholding agent is suspected of preparing, attempting or committing, together with references to corresponding provisions of the Criminal Code. </inglise>
<eesti>Ettekirjutuses tuleb &auml;ra n&auml;idata ka eesm&auml;rk, mida maksumaksja v&otilde;i maksu kinnipidaja tegevuskoha kontrollimisega taotletakse, ning p&otilde;hjus, miks seda eesm&auml;rki ei ole v&otilde;imalik saavutada muid seaduses etten&auml;htud v&otilde;imalusi kasutades. </eesti>
<inglise>The objective behind inspection of the place of business of a taxpayer or withholding agent and the reason why such objective cannot be achieved utilising other possibilities prescribed by law shall also be indicated in the precept. </inglise>
<eesti>(12.04.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.04.2000 entered into force 01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ikes s&auml;testatud kontrollimine toimub f&uuml;&uuml;silisest isikust ettev&otilde;tja, tema esindaja v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;taja, juriidilise isiku v&otilde;i asutuse puhul aga selle esindaja, t&ouml;&ouml;taja v&otilde;i teenistuja juuresolekul. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The inspection prescribed in subsection (1) of this section shall be carried out in the presence of the sole proprietor or his or her representative or employee or, in the case of a legal person or agency, in the presence of a representative or employee of the enterprise. </inglise>
<eesti>(10.04.96 j&otilde;ust.12.05.96 - RT I 1996, 29, 577; 12.04.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </eesti>
<inglise>(10.04.96 entered into force 12.05.96 - RT I 1996, 29, 577; 12.04.2000 entered into force 01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Maksuhalduri ametnikul on &otilde;igus v&otilde;tta mootorik&uuml;tusena kasutatava k&uuml;tuse erim&auml;rgistatuse kindlakstegemiseks s&otilde;idukite k&uuml;tusepaakidest ja mujalt k&uuml;tuses&uuml;steemist proove. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Officials of the tax authority have the right to take samples from the fuel tanks and elsewhere in the fuel system of motor vehicles to ascertain whether fuel used as motor fuel is fiscally marked. </inglise>
<eesti>(23.09.97 j&otilde;ust.01.01.98 - RT I 1997, 73, 1201; 12.04.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </eesti>
<inglise>(23.09.97 entered into force 01.01.98 - RT I 1997, 73, 1201; 12.04.2000 entered into force 01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 17. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 17. </inglise>
<eesti>Maksumaksja ja maksu kinnipidaja majandustegevuse dokumentide kontrollimine </eesti>
<inglise>Verification of documents concerning economic activities of taxpayers and withholding agents </inglise>
<eesti>(12.04.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.04.2000 entered into force 01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Maksuhalduri ametnikul on &otilde;igus talle maksuhalduri keskasutuse peadirektori, kohaliku asutuse direktori v&otilde;i nende aset&auml;itjate poolt antud volituse alusel kontrollida juriidilise isiku, asutuse v&otilde;i f&uuml;&uuml;silisest isikust ettev&otilde;tja k&otilde;iki dokumente, mis on vajalikud maksumaksja maksude tasumise v&otilde;i maksude kinnipidamise &otilde;igsuse kontrollimiseks, tema poolt tasumisele v&otilde;i kinnipidamisele kuuluva maksusumma m&auml;&auml;ramiseks v&otilde;i maksuv&otilde;la sissen&otilde;udmiseks, samuti teha kaupade, materjalide ja muu vara ning tehtud t&ouml;&ouml;de ja osutatud teenuste inventuure ja &uuml;lem&otilde;&otilde;tmisi. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An official of a tax authority has the right, pursuant to authorisation issued to him or her by the director general of the central tax authority, the director of a local office of the tax authority or a deputy thereof, to inspect all the documents of a legal person, agency or sole proprietor which are required in order to verify the correctness of the payment or withholding of taxes of the taxpayer, to assess the amount of tax to be paid or withheld by the taxpayer or to collect tax arrears, and also to take inventory or control measurements of goods, materials, other assets, work performed and services provided. </inglise>
<eesti>(10.04.96 j&otilde;ust.12.05.96 - RT I 1996, 29, 577; 17.02.99 j&otilde;ust.01.04.99 - RT I 1999, 27, 394; 12.04.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </eesti>
<inglise>(10.04.96 entered into force 12.05.96 - RT I 1996, 29, 577; 17.02.99 entered into force 01.04.99 - RT I 1999, 27, 394; 12.04.2000 entered into force 01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Maksuhalduril on &otilde;igus teha k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1.l&otilde;ikes nimetatud dokumentidest v&auml;ljav&otilde;tteid, &auml;rakirju ja koopiaid. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Tax authorities have the right to make extracts, transcripts and copies of the documents specified in subsection (1) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(2 (1)) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ikes nimetatud dokumentide kontrollimise, inventuuri v&otilde;i &uuml;lem&otilde;&otilde;tmise kohta koostab kontrolli l&auml;biviinud maksuhalduri ametnik kontrollakti, milles tuuakse &auml;ra k&otilde;ik kontrolli k&auml;igus tuvastatud, tasumisele kuuluva maksusumma m&auml;&auml;ramise v&otilde;i maksuv&otilde;la sissen&otilde;udmise seisukohalt t&auml;hendust omavad asjaolud. </eesti>
<inglise>(2 (1)) The official of the tax authority who conducts the inspection shall prepare a report regarding the verification of documents and the inventory or control measurements specified in subsection (1) of this section, and all facts which are ascertained in the course of the inspection and which are relevant to determination of the amount of tax to be paid or to collection of tax arrears shall be indicated in the report. </inglise>
<eesti>Maksumaksjal v&otilde;i maksu kinnipidajal on &otilde;igus tutvuda nimetatud aktiga ning selles toodud asjaoludega mitten&otilde;ustumise korral n&otilde;uda oma eriarvamuse m&auml;rkimist kontrollakti. </eesti>
<inglise>The taxpayer or withholding agent has the right to examine the specified report and, in the event of disagreement with the facts indicated therein, to demand inclusion of the taxpayer's or withholding agent's dissenting opinion in the report. </inglise>
<eesti>(12.04.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.04.2000 entered into force 01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui maksuhaldur avastab maksumaksja kontrollimisel kriminaalkuriteo v&otilde;i haldus&otilde;iguserikkumise tunnused, on tal &otilde;igus &auml;ra v&otilde;tta asjasse puutuvaid dokumente, koostades &auml;rav&otilde;tmise kohta protokolli vastavalt haldus&otilde;iguserikkumiste seadustikus s&auml;testatule. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If a tax authority discovers evidence of a criminal or administrative offence upon inspection of a taxpayer, the tax authority has the right to remove the documents concerned, provided a report on the removal is prepared pursuant to the provisions of the Code of Administrative Offences. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 18. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 18. </inglise>
<eesti>M&otilde;&otilde;turite ja t&otilde;kendite paigaldamine </eesti>
<inglise>Installation of meters and preventive measures </inglise>
<eesti>Maksukorralduse seaduse v&otilde;i maksuseaduse rikkumise t&otilde;kestamiseks ning maksumaksja poolt maksude tasumise &otilde;igsuse kontrollimiseks v&otilde;i tema poolt tasumisele kuuluva maksusumma m&auml;&auml;ramiseks on maksuhalduril maksumaksja teadmisel &otilde;igus: </eesti>
<inglise>In order to prevent violation of the Taxation Act or a tax Act and to verify the correctness of the tax payments of a taxpayer or to assess the amount of tax to be paid by a taxpayer, tax authorities have the right, with the knowledge of the taxpayer, to: </inglise>
<eesti>(12.04.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.04.2000 entered into force 01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </inglise>
<eesti>1) paigaldada mahutitele, hoidlatele ja seadmetele m&otilde;&otilde;tureid v&otilde;i seaduses s&auml;testatud juhtudel n&otilde;uda maksumaksjalt nende paigaldamist; </eesti>
<inglise>1) install meters on receptacles, storages and equipment or to require the taxpayer to install meters in the cases provided by law; </inglise>
<eesti>2) plommida v&otilde;i pitseerida mahuteid, hoidlaid, ruume ja seadmeid, samuti hasartm&auml;ngu korraldamisel kasutatavat m&auml;nguinventari; </eesti>
<inglise>2) seal or stamp receptacles, storages, rooms and equipment, and gambling inventory if gambling is being organised; </inglise>
<eesti>3) sulgeda territooriume v&otilde;i nende osasid. </eesti>
<inglise>3) close off territories or parts thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>(06.12.95 j&otilde;ust.01.02.96 - RT I 1995, 95, 1630; 10.04.96 j&otilde;ust.12.05.96 - RT I 1996, 29, 577) </eesti>
<inglise>(06.12.95 entered into force 01.02.96 - RT I 1995, 95, 1630; 10.04.96 entered into force 21.05.93 - RT I 1996, 29, 577) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 19. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 19. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;igus saada teavet maksumaksjalt ja maksu kinnipidajalt </eesti>
<inglise>Right to obtain information from taxpayers and withholding agents </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Maksuhalduril on maksude tasumise v&otilde;i kinnipidamise &otilde;igsuse kontrollimiseks v&otilde;i tasumisele kuuluva maksusumma m&auml;&auml;ramiseks &otilde;igus n&otilde;uda maksumaksjalt v&otilde;i maksu kinnipidajalt sellekohase ettekirjutusega: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In order to verify the correctness of taxes paid or withheld or to assess the amount of tax to be paid, a tax authority has the right to issue a precept to require the taxpayer or withholding agent to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) suuliste v&otilde;i kirjalike seletuste andmist; </eesti>
<inglise>1) provide oral or written explanations; </inglise>
<eesti>2) asjade, raha v&otilde;i v&auml;&auml;rtpaberite etten&auml;itamist; </eesti>
<inglise>2) present things, money or securities; </inglise>
<eesti>3) dokumentide esitamist, mis sisaldavad maksude tasumise &otilde;igsuse kontrollimiseks v&otilde;i tasumisele kuuluva maksusumma m&auml;&auml;ramiseks vajalikke andmeid. </eesti>
<inglise>3) submit documents which contain information necessary for verification of the correctness of taxes paid or to assess the amount of tax to be paid. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Maksuhalduril on &otilde;igus n&otilde;uda sellekohase ettekirjutuse alusel maksumaksja v&otilde;i maksu kinnipidaja ilmumist maksuhalduri t&ouml;&ouml;ajal tema ruumidesse suuliste seletuste andmiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A tax authority has the right, pursuant to a corresponding precept, to require the taxpayer or withholding agent to appear at the premises of the tax authority during the working hours of the tax authority to provide oral explanations. </inglise>
<eesti>Vajadusel selgitab maksuhaldur maksumaksjale v&otilde;i maksu kinnipidajale tema &otilde;igusi ja kohustusi. </eesti>
<inglise>If necessary, the tax authority shall explain the rights and obligations of the taxpayer or withholding agent to the taxpayer or withholding agent. </inglise>
<eesti>Selgitamise kohta tehakse m&auml;rge protokolli. </eesti>
<inglise>A notation concerning explanation shall be made in the minutes. </inglise>
<eesti>Suulised seletused protokollitakse ning protokollile v&otilde;etakse maksumaksja v&otilde;i maksu kinnipidaja v&otilde;i tema esindaja allkiri. </eesti>
<inglise>Oral explanations shall be recorded in the minutes and signed by the taxpayer or withholding agent or by a representative of the taxpayer or withholding agent. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui maksumaksja, maksu kinnipidaja v&otilde;i tema esindaja keeldub protokollile alla kirjutamast, tehakse protokolli m&auml;rge allakirjutamisest keeldumise ning selle motiivide kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>If the taxpayer or withholding agent or the representative of the taxpayer or withholding agent refuses to sign the minutes, a notation concerning such refusal shall be made in the minutes and the reasons for refusal shall be set out in the minutes. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ikes nimetatud dokumentide ja esemete etten&auml;itamine toimub maksuhalduri ametiruumides, v&auml;lja arvatud juhul, kui esemete v&otilde;i dokumentide vaatlemiseks ja kontrollimiseks maksumaksja v&otilde;i maksu kinnipidaja juures on saadud tema n&otilde;usolek v&otilde;i kui dokumentide v&otilde;i esemete maksuhalduri ametiruumidesse toimetamine on v&otilde;imatu v&otilde;i p&otilde;hjustaks maksumaksjale v&otilde;i maksu kinnipidajale &uuml;lem&auml;&auml;raseid ebamugavusi v&otilde;i kulutusi. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Presentation of documents and objects specified in subsection (1) of this section shall be carried out in the offices of the tax authority, unless the taxpayer or withholding agent has granted consent to the examination and inspection of objects and documents on the premises of the taxpayer or withholding agent or unless conveyance of the documents or objects to the office of the tax authority is impossible or would cause the taxpayer or withholding agent excessive inconvenience or expense. </inglise>
<eesti>Raha etten&auml;itamine toimub maksumaksja v&otilde;i maksu kinnipidaja juures. </eesti>
<inglise>Presentation of money shall be carried out on the premises of the taxpayer or withholding agent. </inglise>
<eesti>(12.04.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.04.2000 entered into force 01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 20. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 20. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;igus saada teavet kolmandatelt isikutelt </eesti>
<inglise>Right to obtain information from third persons </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Maksude tasumise, kinnipidamise ja &uuml;lekandmise &otilde;igsuse kontrollimiseks ja maksumaksja poolt tasumisele ning maksu kinnipidaja poolt kinnipidamisele kuuluva maksusumma m&auml;&auml;ramiseks ja maksuv&otilde;la sissen&otilde;udmiseks on maksuhalduril ettekirjutuse alusel &otilde;igus saada ettekirjutuses n&auml;idatud t&auml;htp&auml;evaks teavet kolmandatelt isikutelt, sealhulgas krediidiasutustelt, samuti n&otilde;uda nende isikute k&auml;sutuses olevate maksumaksja ja maksu kinnipidaja kohta k&auml;ivate dokumentide esitamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In order to verify the correctness of the payment, withholding or transfer of taxes, to determine the amount of tax to be paid by a taxpayer or to be withheld by a withholding agent, or to collect tax arrears, tax authorities have the right, pursuant to a precept, to obtain information from third persons, including credit institutions, by the due date indicated in the precept and to require third persons to submit such documents as are at their disposal concerning the taxpayer or the withholding agent. </inglise>
<eesti>(10.04.96 j&otilde;ust.12.05.96 - RT I 1996, 29, 577; 12.04.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </eesti>
<inglise>(10.04.96 entered into force 12.05.96 - RT I 1996, 29, 577; 12.04.2000 entered into force 01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ike alusel teabe andmisest on &otilde;igus keelduda: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The following have the right to refuse to provide information under subsection (1) of this section: </inglise>
<eesti>1) advokaadil ja advokatuuri t&ouml;&ouml;tajal asjaolude kohta, mis said temale teatavaks seoses &otilde;igusabi andmise v&otilde;i muude t&ouml;&ouml;&uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmisega; </eesti>
<inglise>1) advocates or employees of the Bar Association concerning circumstances which become known to them in connection with the provision of legal assistance or the performance of other duties of employment; </inglise>
<eesti>2) notaril, vaimulikul ja arstil temale seoses kutse- v&otilde;i ametitegevusega teatavaks saanud andmete kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>2) notaries, ministers of religion and doctors concerning information which becomes known to them in connection with their professional activities; </inglise>
<eesti>3) riikliku statistilise vaatluse korraldajal temale seoses vaatlusega teatavaks saanud andmete kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>3) agencies conducting state statistical surveys concerning information which becomes known to them in connection with a survey; </inglise>
<eesti>4) audiitoril ja audiitori kutsetegevusega seotud isikul vastavalt audiitortegevuse seaduse (RT I 1999, 24, 360) &sect; 38 l&otilde;ikele 1; </eesti>
<inglise>4) auditors and persons involved in the professional activities of an auditor, pursuant to subsection 38 (1) of the Authorised Public Accountants Act (RT I 1999, 24, 360); </inglise>
<eesti>5) maksumaksja v&otilde;i maksu kinnipidaja abikaasal, otsejoones sugulasel, &otilde;el v&otilde;i vennal, &otilde;e v&otilde;i venna alanejal sugulasel, abikaasa otsejoones sugulasel, abikaasa &otilde;el v&otilde;i vennal, v&auml;lja arvatud juhul, kui ta vastavalt k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 19 s&auml;testatule peab antud asjas informatsiooni andma ja dokumente esitama seoses enda maksukohustusega; </eesti>
<inglise>5) spouses, direct blood relatives, sisters or brothers of taxpayers or withholding agents, descendants of sisters or brothers of taxpayers or withholding agents, and direct blood relatives or sisters or brothers of spouses of taxpayers or withholding agents, unless such persons are required to provide information in the given matter and submit documents in connection with their own tax liability pursuant to provisions of &sect; 19 of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>6) esindajal seoses talle esindusega teatavaks saanud asjaolude kohta, v&auml;lja arvatud esindaja poolt esindatava nimel k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 19 nimetatud kohustuste t&auml;itmise korral. </eesti>
<inglise>6) representatives concerning circumstances which become known to them in connection with representation, except upon the performance of obligations specified in &sect; 19 of this Act by the representative in the name of the person represented. </inglise>
<eesti>(12.04.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.04.2000 entered into force 01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Riiklike maksude maksuhalduril on &otilde;igus ettekirjutuse alusel saada tasuta selles etten&auml;htud t&auml;htp&auml;evaks riikliku registri vastutavalt v&otilde;i volitatud t&ouml;&ouml;tlejalt ettekirjutuses n&auml;idatud perioodil maksustamise seisukohast t&auml;hendust omavaid tehinguid sooritanud isikuid identifitseerivaid andmeid (ees- ja perekonnanimi v&otilde;i &auml;rinimi; isiku- v&otilde;i registrikood, isikukoodi puudumisel s&uuml;nnikuup&auml;ev, -kuu ja -aasta). </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The tax authorities for state taxes have the right, pursuant to a precept, to obtain, without charge and by the due date indicated in the precept, information from the chief or authorised processor of a state register which identifies persons (given name and surname or business name, personal identification code or registry code or, in the absence of a personal identification code, date of birth) who concluded transactions relevant to taxation during the period indicated in the precept. </inglise>
<eesti>(12.04.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.04.2000 entered into force 01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kui k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. v&otilde;i 3. l&otilde;ikes nimetatud ettekirjutusega antud t&auml;htaeg ei ole ettekirjutuse adressaadi arvates temale pandud kohustuse t&auml;itmiseks piisav, v&otilde;ib ta taotleda maksuhaldurilt t&auml;htaja pikendamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If the addressee of a precept specified in subsection (1) or (3) of this section does not consider the term prescribed by the precept sufficient for performance of the obligation imposed on the addressee, the addressee may apply to the tax authority for extension of the term. </inglise>
<eesti>(12.04.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.04.2000 entered into force 01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </inglise>
<eesti>(5) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 2. l&otilde;ike punktis 5 nimetatud isikutelt teabe n&otilde;udmise korral tuleb neid kirjalikult v&otilde;i allkirja vastu suuliselt teavitada &otilde;igusest dokumentide esitamisest v&otilde;i teabe andmisest keelduda. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) If information is requested from persons specified in clause (2) 5) of this section, such persons shall be informed in writing or orally against a signature of the right to refuse to submit documents or provide information. </inglise>
<eesti>(12.04.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.04.2000 entered into force 01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 21. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 21. </inglise>
<eesti>Maksuteade </eesti>
<inglise>Tax notice </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui k&auml;esolev seadus, maksuseadus v&otilde;i selle alusel kehtestatud &otilde;igusakt paneb maksusumma arvutamise kohustuse maksuhaldurile, v&auml;ljastab maksuhalduri kohalik asutus tasumisele kuuluva maksusumma kohta maksuteate. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If this Act, a tax Act or legislation issued on the basis thereof imposes the obligation to calculate the amount of tax on a tax authority, a local office of the tax authority shall issue a tax notice concerning the amount of tax due. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Maksuteates peavad olema j&auml;rgmised andmed: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A tax notice shall set out the following information: </inglise>
<eesti>1) maksuhalduri nimetus ja aadress; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the name and address of the tax authority; </inglise>
<eesti>2) maksuteate koostanud ametniku nimi ja ametikoht; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the name and position of the official who prepared the tax notice; </inglise>
<eesti>3) maksuteate koostamise kuup&auml;ev; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the date of preparation of the tax notice; </inglise>
<eesti>4) maksumaksja v&otilde;i maksu kinnipidaja nimi ja aadress; </eesti>
<inglise>4) the name and address of the taxpayer or withholding agent; </inglise>
<eesti>5) viide &otilde;igusakti s&auml;ttele, mille alusel maksusumma on arvutatud ja maksuteade v&auml;ljastatakse; </eesti>
<inglise>5) a reference to the provisions of legislation on the basis of which the amount of tax is calculated and the tax notice is issued; </inglise>
<eesti>6) tasumisele kuuluv maksusumma; </eesti>
<inglise>6) the amount of tax due; </inglise>
<eesti>7) maksusumma tasumise t&auml;htaeg. </eesti>
<inglise>7) the term for payment of the amount of tax. </inglise>
<eesti>8) maksuteate vaidlustamise kord. </eesti>
<inglise>8) the procedure for contesting the tax notice. </inglise>
<eesti>(12.04.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.04.2000 entered into force 01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Maksu ei m&auml;&auml;rata ja maksuteadet ei v&auml;ljastata, kui maksusumma on alla 50 krooni. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A tax shall not be imposed and a tax notice shall not be issued if the amount of tax is less than 50 kroons. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Maksuteatele kirjutab alla maksuhalduri kohaliku asutuse direktor v&otilde;i selleks volitatud ametnik ning see saadetakse maksumaksjale v&otilde;i maksu kinnipidajale postiga hiljemalt 30 kalendrip&auml;eva enne maksu tasumise t&auml;htp&auml;eva. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A tax notice shall be signed by the director of the local office of a tax authority or an official authorised therefor and sent to a taxpayer or withholding agent by post not later than thirty calendar days prior to the due date for payment of the tax. </inglise>
<eesti>(15.09.99 j&otilde;ust.09.10.99 - RT I 1999, 71, 685; 12.04.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </eesti>
<inglise>(15.09.99 entered into force 09.10.99 - RT I 1999, 71, 685; 12.04.2000 entered into force 01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 22. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 22. </inglise>
<eesti>Maksusumma m&auml;&auml;ramine maksuhalduri poolt </eesti>
<inglise>Assessment of amount of tax by tax authority </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Maksuhalduril on &otilde;igus m&auml;&auml;rata tasumisele v&otilde;i &uuml;lekandmisele kuuluv maksusumma maksumaksjale v&otilde;i maksu kinnipidajale, kes ei ole esitanud maksudeklaratsiooni etten&auml;htud t&auml;htp&auml;evaks v&otilde;i kelle kohta on maksuhalduril andmed, et tema poolt maksudeklaratsioonis n&auml;idatud v&otilde;i tema poolt maksudeklaratsiooni kantud andmete alusel maksuhalduri poolt k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 21 1. l&otilde;ikes s&auml;testatud korras arvutatud maksusumma on v&auml;iksem maksusummast, mis oleks tulnud tasuda v&otilde;i &uuml;le kanda vastavalt maksuseadusele. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A tax authority has the right to assess the amount of tax to be paid or transferred by a taxpayer or a withholding agent who has not filed a tax return by the prescribed due date or concerning whom the tax authority has information that the amount of tax indicated by the taxpayer or the withholding agent in the taxpayer's tax return or calculated by the tax authority pursuant to the procedure provided for in subsection 21 (1) of this Act on the basis of the information entered in the tax return by the taxpayer or withholding agent is less than the amount of tax which should have been paid or transferred according to a tax Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(12.04.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.04.2000 entered into force 01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui maksuseaduses pole s&auml;testatud teisiti, v&otilde;ib maksuhaldur maksumaksja v&otilde;i maksu kinnipidaja poolt tasumisele v&otilde;i &uuml;lekandmisele kuuluva maksusumma m&auml;&auml;rata kolme aasta jooksul, maksusumma tahtliku tasumata v&otilde;i &uuml;le kandmata j&auml;tmise korral kuue aasta jooksul maksudeklaratsiooni esitamise t&auml;htp&auml;evast arvates. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Unless otherwise provided by a tax Act, a tax authority may determine the amount of tax to be paid or to be transferred by a taxpayer or a withholding agent within three years or, in the event of intentional failure to pay or transfer tax, within six years after the due date for submission of a tax return. </inglise>
<eesti>(12.04.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.04.2000 entered into force 01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Tasumisele v&otilde;i &uuml;lekandmisele kuuluva maksusumma m&auml;&auml;ramisel on maksuhaldur kohustatud ettekirjutuses n&auml;itama maksusumma m&auml;&auml;ramise aluseks olnud metoodika. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Upon assessment of an amount of tax to be paid or transferred, a tax authority is required to indicate the method used to determine the amount of tax in the precept. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Maksuhalduri m&auml;&auml;ratud maksusumma vaidlustamise korral lasub maksumaksjal v&otilde;i maksu kinnipidajal kohustus t&otilde;estada, et maks m&auml;&auml;rati valesti. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If an amount of tax assessed by a tax authority is contested, the burden of proof that a tax was assessed incorrectly lies with the taxpayer or the withholding agent. </inglise>
<eesti>(23.10.96 j&otilde;ust.24.11.96 - RT I 1996, 78, 1379) </eesti>
<inglise>(23.10.96 entered into force 24.11.96 - RT I 1996, 78, 1379) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 23. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 23. </inglise>
<eesti>Maksuv&otilde;la tasumise t&auml;htaeg </eesti>
<inglise>Term for payment of tax arrears </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 22 alusel tasumisele kuuluva maksusumma m&auml;&auml;ramisel maksuhalduri poolt peab maksumaksja v&otilde;i maksu kinnipidaja ettekirjutuses m&auml;rgitud summa tasuma 30 kalendrip&auml;eva jooksul ettekirjutuse saamise p&auml;evale j&auml;rgnevast p&auml;evast arvates. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Upon determination by a tax authority of an amount of tax to be paid on the basis of &sect; 22 of this Act, a taxpayer or withholding agent shall pay the amount indicated in the precept within thirty days as of the date following the date of receipt of the precept. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Maksuhalduril on &otilde;igus teha ettekirjutus maksumaksjale v&otilde;i maksu kinnipidajale maksuv&otilde;la tasumiseks 10 kalendrip&auml;eva jooksul, arvates ettekirjutuse saamise p&auml;evale j&auml;rgnevast p&auml;evast, kui maksumaksja v&otilde;i maksu kinnipidaja ei ole enda poolt deklareeritud v&otilde;i k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 21 alusel maksuhalduri poolt v&auml;ljastatud maksuteates n&auml;idatud v&otilde;i tolliv&otilde;last tulenevat maksusummat t&auml;htp&auml;evaks tasunud. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A tax authority has the right to issue a precept to a taxpayer or withholding agent for the payment of tax arrears within ten calendar days as of the date following the date of receipt of the precept if the taxpayer or withholding agent fails to pay the amount of tax declared by the taxpayer or withholding agent or indicated in a tax notice issued by the tax authority on the basis of &sect; 21 of this Act or the amount of a customs debt by the due date for payment. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui maksumaksja ei ole tasunud tolliv&otilde;last tulenevat maksusummat t&auml;htp&auml;evaks v&otilde;i t&auml;itnud talle k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 2. l&otilde;ike alusel tehtud ettekirjutust, v&otilde;ib Tolliamet teha garandile v&otilde;i garandile ja maksumaksjale samaaegselt ettekirjutuse maksuv&otilde;la tasumiseks 10 kalendrip&auml;eva jooksul, arvates ettekirjutuse saamise p&auml;evale j&auml;rgnevast p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If a taxpayer fails to pay the amount of a customs debt by the due date or fails to comply with a precept issued to the taxpayer on the basis of subsection (2) of this section, the Customs Board may issue a precept to the guarantor or to the guarantor and the taxpayer simultaneously for payment of the tax arrears within ten calendar days as of the date following the date of receipt of the precept. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Maksuametil ja tema kohalikel asutustel on &otilde;igus teha garandile ettekirjutus maksuv&otilde;la tasumiseks 30 kalendrip&auml;eva jooksul, arvates ettekirjutuse saamise p&auml;evale j&auml;rgnevast p&auml;evast, kui maksumaksja ei t&auml;ida maksuv&otilde;la tasumise ajakava. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The tax Board and its local offices have the right to issue a precept to the guarantor for the payment of tax arrears within thirty calendar days as of the date following the date of receipt of the precept if a taxpayer does not meet the schedule for payment of the tax arrears. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Maksuhalduril on &otilde;igus teha maksumaksjale v&otilde;i maksu kinnipidajale ettekirjutus maksuv&otilde;la tasumiseks kahe kalendrip&auml;eva jooksul, arvates ettekirjutuse saamise p&auml;evale j&auml;rgnevast p&auml;evast, kui maksuhalduril on p&otilde;hjendatud kahtlus, et maksuv&otilde;la sissen&otilde;udmisega viivitamine v&otilde;ib muuta v&otilde;la hilisema sissen&otilde;udmise v&otilde;imatuks. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) A tax authority has the right to issue a precept to a taxpayer or withholding agent for the payment of tax arrears within two calendar days as of the date following the date of receipt of the precept if the tax authority has good reason to believe that any delay in the collection of tax arrears may render later collection of the tax arrears impossible. </inglise>
<eesti>(12.04.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.04.2000 entered into force 01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 23 (1). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 23 (1). </inglise>
<eesti>Maksuv&otilde;la sissen&otilde;udmine kolmandalt isikult </eesti>
<inglise>Collection of tax arrears from third persons </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Maksuhalduril on &otilde;igus ettekirjutusega n&otilde;uda maksumaksja v&otilde;i maksu kinnipidaja maksuv&otilde;la tasumist 30 p&auml;eva jooksul, arvates ettekirjutuse k&auml;ttesaamise p&auml;evale j&auml;rgnevast p&auml;evast: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A tax authority has the right to require, by a precept, payment of the tax arrears of a taxpayer or withholding agent within thirty calendar days as of the date following the date of receipt of the precept: </inglise>
<eesti>1) ettev&otilde;tte v&otilde;i selle osa &uuml;leandnud isikult sellise maksuv&otilde;la osas, mille eest ta vastutab solidaarselt ettev&otilde;tte omandajaga vastavalt &auml;riseadustiku &sect;-le 5; </eesti>
<inglise>1) from a person who transfers an enterprise or a part thereof with regard to such tax arrears for which the transferor and the transferee are solidarily liable pursuant to &sect; 5 of the Commercial Code; </inglise>
<eesti>2) t&auml;is&uuml;hingu osanikult v&otilde;i usaldus&uuml;hingu t&auml;isosanikult t&auml;is- v&otilde;i usaldus&uuml;hingu maksuv&otilde;la osas, mille eest osanik vastutab vastavalt &auml;riseadustiku &sect;-dele 101 ning 102; </eesti>
<inglise>2) from a partner of a general partnership or a general partner of a limited partnership with regard to tax arrears of the general partnership or limited partnership for which the partner is liable pursuant to &sect;&sect; 101 and 102 of the Commercial Code; </inglise>
<eesti>3) usaldus&uuml;hingu usaldusosanikult usaldus&uuml;hingu sellise maksuv&otilde;la osas, mille eest usaldusosanik vastutab vastavalt &auml;riseadustiku &sect;-le 132; </eesti>
<inglise>3) from a limited partner of a limited partnership with regard to such tax arrears of the limited partnership for which the limited partner is liable pursuant to &sect; 132 of the Commercial Code; </inglise>
<eesti>4) &uuml;histu liikmelt &uuml;histu sellise maksuv&otilde;la osas, mille eest &uuml;histu liige vastutab vastavalt Eesti Vabariigi &uuml;histuseaduse (RT 1992, 36, 477; RT I 1998, 95, 1513; 1999, 10, 155) &sect;-le 19. </eesti>
<inglise>4) from a member of an association with regard to such tax arrears of the association for which the member of the association is liable pursuant to &sect; 19 of the Republic of Estonia Associations Act (RT 1992, 36, 477; RT I 1998, 95, 1513; 1999, 10, 155). </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ikes s&auml;testatud juhtudel v&otilde;ib ettekirjutuse teha p&auml;rast seda, kui maksumaksja v&otilde;i maksu kinnipidaja suhtes on alustatud sissen&otilde;udmist k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 24 1. l&otilde;ike punktis 1 s&auml;testatud viisil ning selle tulemusena ei ole kolme kuu jooksul &otilde;nnestunud maksuv&otilde;lga t&auml;ies ulatuses sisse n&otilde;uda, v&otilde;i p&auml;rast maksumaksja v&otilde;i maksu kinnipidaja pankroti v&auml;ljakuulutamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Precepts may be issued in the cases provided for in subsection (1) of this section after commencement of collection in the manner provided for in clause 24 (1) 1) of this Act with respect to a taxpayer or withholding agent and if, as a result thereof, the tax arrears are not collected in full within three months, or after the taxpayer or withholding agent is declared bankrupt. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ikes s&auml;testatud juhtudel vastutab mitu isikut maksuv&otilde;la tasumise eest solidaarselt, v&otilde;ib maksuhaldur neile teha &uuml;hise ettekirjutuse. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If, in cases provided for in subsection (1) of this section, several persons are solidarily liable for the payment of tax arrears, the tax authority may issue a joint precept to such persons. </inglise>
<eesti>(12.04.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.04.2000 entered into force 01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 24. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 24. </inglise>
<eesti>Maksuhalduri &otilde;igused maksuv&otilde;la sissen&otilde;udmisel </eesti>
<inglise>Rights of tax authority in collection of tax arrears </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui maksumaksja v&otilde;i maksu kinnipidaja ei ole maksuhalduri ettekirjutuses m&auml;&auml;ratud t&auml;htaja jooksul maksuv&otilde;lga tasunud v&otilde;i &uuml;le kandnud, on maksuhalduril &otilde;igus: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If a taxpayer or withholding agent does not pay or transfer tax arrears during the term specified in a precept of a tax authority, the tax authority has the right to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) teha maksuv&otilde;la sissen&otilde;udmiseks krediidiasutusele ettekirjutus maksumaksja v&otilde;i maksu kinnipidaja pangakonto(de) arestimiseks v&otilde;i tema pangakonto(de) lt vastuvaidlematus korras raha &uuml;lekandmiseks maksuhalduri pangakontole maksuv&otilde;la summa suuruses; </eesti>
<inglise>1) issue, for the collection of such tax arrears, a precept to credit institutions for the seizure of the bank account(s) of the taxpayer or withholding agent or for the mandatory transfer of money from the bank account(s) of the taxpayer or withholding agent to the bank account of the tax authority in the amount of the tax arrears; </inglise>
<eesti>(17.02.99 j&otilde;ust.01.04.99 - RT I 1999, 27, 394) </eesti>
<inglise>(17.02.99 entered into force 01.04.99 - RT I 1999, 27, 394) </inglise>
<eesti>2) p&ouml;&ouml;rduda maa- v&otilde;i linnakohtu t&auml;itevosakonna poole maksumaksja ja maksu kinnipidaja maksuv&otilde;la sissen&otilde;udmiseks t&auml;itemenetluse seadustikus etten&auml;htud korras; </eesti>
<inglise>2) have recourse to the enforcement department of a county or city court for the collection of the tax arrears of the taxpayer or withholding agent pursuant to the procedure prescribed in the Code of Enforcement Procedure; </inglise>
<eesti>(19.03.97 j&otilde;ust.25.04.97 - RT I 1997, 29, 447) </eesti>
<inglise>(19.03.97 entered into force 25.04.97 - RT I 1997, 29, 447) </inglise>
<eesti>(10.06.97 j&otilde;ust.10.07.97 - RT I 1997, 48, 778) </eesti>
<inglise>(10.06.97 entered into force 10.07.97 - RT I 1997, 48, 778) </inglise>
<eesti>3) (Kehtetu - 12.04.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </eesti>
<inglise>3) (Repealed - 12.04.2000 entered into force 01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Maksumaksja v&otilde;i maksu kinnipidaja varale v&otilde;ib p&ouml;&ouml;rata sissen&otilde;uet seitsme aasta jooksul, arvates p&auml;evast, mil maksusumma oleks tulnud maksuseaduse alusel tasuda v&otilde;i &uuml;le kanda, rakendades selleks t&auml;itemenetluse seadustikus s&auml;testatud korda. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A claim for payment may be made against the assets of a taxpayer or withholding agent within seven years after the date on which a tax is due on the basis of the Act concerning such tax, pursuant to the procedure provided for in the Code of Enforcement Procedure. </inglise>
<eesti>(23.10.96 j&otilde;ust.24.11.96 - RT I 1996, 78, 1379) </eesti>
<inglise>(23.10.96 entered into force 24.11.96 - RT I 1996, 78, 1379) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 25. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 25. </inglise>
<eesti>Maksumaksja ja maksu kinnipidaja pangakontode arestimine </eesti>
<inglise>Seizure of bank accounts of taxpayer or withholding agent </inglise>
<eesti>(23.10.96 j&otilde;ust.24.11.96 - RT I 1996, 78, 1379) </eesti>
<inglise>(23.10.96 entered into force 24.11.96 - RT I 1996, 78, 1379) </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Krediidiasutus on kohustatud v&otilde;tma maksuhalduri ettekirjutuse maksumaksja v&otilde;i maksu kinnipidaja pangakontolt maksuv&otilde;la maksuhalduri pangakontole &uuml;lekandmise v&otilde;i tema pangakontode arestimise kohta viivitamatult t&auml;itmiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A credit institution is required to promptly comply with a precept of a tax authority for the transfer of tax arrears from the bank account of a taxpayer or withholding agent to the bank account of the tax authority or for the seizure of the bank account of such taxpayer or withholding agent. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui pangakontol olev summa on maksuhalduri ettekirjutuse j&auml;rgi &uuml;lekandmisele kuuluvast summast v&auml;iksem, on krediidiasutus kohustatud t&auml;itma maksuv&otilde;la &uuml;lekandmise ettekirjutuse maksumaksja v&otilde;i maksu kinnipidaja pangakontol oleva summa ulatuses ning edaspidistel laekumistel v&otilde;lgniku pangakontole kandma raha &uuml;le maksuhalduri pangakontole kuni ettekirjutuses m&auml;rgitud summa tasumiseni, v&auml;lja arvatud juhul, kui maksuhaldur on teinud ettekirjutuse arestitud pangakonto avamise kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>If the amount in a bank account is smaller than the amount to be transferred according to a precept of the tax authority, the credit institution is required to comply with the precept for the transfer of the tax arrears in an amount equal to the amount in the bank account of the taxpayer or withholding agent and, upon future receipt in the bank account of the debtor, transfer the money to the bank account of the tax authority until the amount indicated in the precept is paid, except if the tax authority has issued a precept concerning access to the seized bank account. </inglise>
<eesti>(17.02.99 j&otilde;ust.01.04.99 - RT I 1999, 27, 394) </eesti>
<inglise>(17.02.99 entered into force 01.04.99 - RT I 1999, 27, 394) </inglise>
<eesti>(1 (1)) F&uuml;&uuml;silise isiku maksuv&otilde;la sissen&otilde;udmise korral v&otilde;i tema pangakontode arestimisel ei kuulu maksuhalduri poolt sissen&otilde;udmisele ega arestimisele igakuiselt summa &uuml;he kuupalga alamm&auml;&auml;ra suuruses v&otilde;lgniku ja iga tema &uuml;lalpeetava perekonnaliikme kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>(1 (1)) In the case of collection of the tax arrears or seizure of the bank accounts of a natural person, the amount of a minimum monthly wage per debtor and each of his or her dependant family members monthly shall not be subject to collection or seizure by a tax authority. </inglise>
<eesti>Maksuhaldur on kohustatud arvutama sissen&otilde;udmisele v&otilde;i arestimisele mittekuuluva summa ning teavitama sellest krediidiasutust. </eesti>
<inglise>A tax authority is required to calculate the amount not subject to collection or seizure and notify the credit institutions of the amount. </inglise>
<eesti>(17.02.99 j&otilde;ust.01.04.99 - RT I 1999, 27, 394) </eesti>
<inglise>(17.02.99 entered into force 01.04.99 - RT I 1999, 27, 394) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Arestitud pangakontodelt v&otilde;ib v&auml;ljamakseid teha ainult maksuhalduri ettekirjutuse alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Payments from a seized bank account may only be made pursuant to a precept of a tax authority. </inglise>
<eesti>Arestitud pangakonto avatakse maksuhalduri ettekirjutuse alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>A seized bank account is accessible pursuant to a precept of a tax authority. </inglise>
<eesti>(10.04.96 j&otilde;ust.12.05.96 - RT I 1996, 29, 577) </eesti>
<inglise>(10.04.96 entered into force 12.05.96 - RT I 1996, 29, 577) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Krediidiasutusel on keelatud avada pangakontot maksumaksjale v&otilde;i maksu kinnipidajale, kelle pangakontode arestimise kohta on saadud maksuhalduri ettekirjutus. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A credit institution is prohibited from providing a taxpayer or withholding agent with access to a bank account if a precept of a tax authority concerning the seizure of the bank accounts of such taxpayer or withholding agent has been received. </inglise>
<eesti>(10.04.96 j&otilde;ust.12.05.96 - RT I 1996, 29, 577; 23.10.96 j&otilde;ust.24.11.96 - RT I 1996, 78, 1379) </eesti>
<inglise>(10.04.96 entered into force 12.05.96 - RT I 1996, 29, 577; 23.10.96 entered into force 24.11.96 - RT I 2000, 78, 1379) </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Krediidiasutus on kohustatud maksumaksja ja maksu kinnipidaja pangakontode arestimisel viivitamatult kirjalikult edastama ettekirjutuse teinud maksuhaldurile j&auml;rgmised andmed: </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Upon seizure of the bank accounts of a taxpayer or withholding agent, the credit institution is required to communicate immediately the following information to the tax authority which issued the precept: </inglise>
<eesti>1) ettekirjutuse vastuv&otilde;tmise kuup&auml;ev ja kellaaeg; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the date and time of receipt of the precept; </inglise>
<eesti>2) ettekirjutuse vastu v&otilde;tnud t&ouml;&ouml;taja nimi ja ametinimetus; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the name and title of the person who received the precept; </inglise>
<eesti>3) pangakonto arestimise kuup&auml;ev ja kellaaeg; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the date and time of seizure of the bank account; </inglise>
<eesti>4) pangakonto j&auml;&auml;k pangakonto arestimise hetkel. </eesti>
<inglise>4) the balance in the bank account at the moment of seizure of the bank account. </inglise>
<eesti>(12.04.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.04.2000 entered into force 01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 26. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 26. </inglise>
<eesti>Ekspordi- ja imporditehingute ning transiitveo peatamine </eesti>
<inglise>Suspension of export and import transactions and transit procedures </inglise>
<eesti>Maksuhalduri ettekirjutuse t&auml;itmata j&auml;tmise korral v&otilde;ib Tolliamet iseseisvalt v&otilde;i Maksuameti ettekirjutuse alusel peatada maksumaksja ekspordi- ja imporditehingud ning transiitveo, pidades kinni maksumaksja poolt &uuml;le Eesti tollipiiri toimetatava kauba ja maksumaksjale kuuluva veoki. </eesti>
<inglise>Upon non-compliance with a precept of a tax authority, the Customs Board may, either independently or pursuant to a precept of the Tax Board, suspend the export and import transactions and transit procedures of the taxpayer by seizing goods being conveyed across the Estonian customs frontier by the taxpayer or the means of transport of the taxpayer. </inglise>
<eesti>(17.10.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.07.2002 - RT I 2001, 88, 531) </eesti>
<inglise>(17.10.2001 entered into force 01.07.2002 - RT I 2001, 88, 531) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 27. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 27. </inglise>
<eesti>T&otilde;kendite k&otilde;rvaldamine </eesti>
<inglise>Removal of preventive measures </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Maksuhaldur on kohustatud k&otilde;rvaldama k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahvi 18 punktide 2 ja 3 v&otilde;i paragrahvide 25 ja 26 alusel rakendatud t&otilde;kendi hiljemalt maksuv&otilde;la tasumisele v&otilde;i t&otilde;kendi rakendamise p&otilde;hjuse k&otilde;rvaldamisele v&otilde;i &auml;ralangemisele j&auml;rgneval t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eval. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A tax authority is required to remove any preventive measure implemented pursuant to clause 18 2) or 3) or &sect;&sect; 25-26 of this Act by the working day following the date of payment of tax arrears or following the day on which the reason for the implementation of the preventive measure is removed or ceases to exist. </inglise>
<eesti>(10.04.96 j&otilde;ust.12.05.96 - RT I 1996, 29, 577) </eesti>
<inglise>(10.04.96 entered into force 12.05.96 - RT I 1996, 29, 577) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Maksuhaldur on kohustatud h&uuml;vitama maksumaksjale otsese kahju, mis tekkis k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 18 punktides 2 v&otilde;i 3 s&auml;testatud tegevuse tagaj&auml;rjel, kui seejuures ei tuvastatud seaduserikkumist maksumaksja poolt v&otilde;i kui maksuhaldur ei t&auml;itnud k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1.l&otilde;ikes s&auml;testatud tingimust. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A tax authority is required to compensate a taxpayer for any direct damage caused as a consequence of the activities provided for in clause 18 2) or 3) of this Act if no offence on the part of the taxpayer is ascertained or if the tax authority fails to comply with the condition provided for in subsection (1) of this section. </inglise>
