<eesti>Vastutus maksuseaduste ja k&auml;esoleva seaduse rikkumise eest </eesti>
<inglise>Liability for Violations of Tax Acts and this Act </inglise>
<eesti>(10.04.96 j&otilde;ust.12.05.96 - RT I 1996, 29, 577) </eesti>
<inglise>(10.04.96 entered into force 12.05.96 - RT I 1996, 29, 577) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 28. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 28. </inglise>
<eesti>Intressid </eesti>
<inglise>Interest </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui maksumaksja poolt tasutud v&otilde;i maksu kinnipidaja poolt &uuml;lekantud maksusumma on v&auml;iksem maksusummast, mida oleks tulnud tasuda v&otilde;i &uuml;le kanda vastavalt maksuseadusele, v&otilde;i maksusumma ei ole t&auml;htp&auml;evaks tasutud v&otilde;i &uuml;le kantud, arvestatakse tasumata v&otilde;i &uuml;lekandmata summalt intressi. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If an amount of tax paid by a taxpayer or transferred by a withholding agent is lower than the amount of tax to be paid or transferred pursuant to a tax Act, or if an amount of tax is not paid or transferred by the due date, interest is calculated on the amount which is outstanding or has not been transferred. </inglise>
<eesti>Intressi arvestatakse alates p&auml;evast, mis j&auml;rgneb p&auml;evale, mil maksu tasumine v&otilde;i &uuml;lekandmine seaduse j&auml;rgi pidi toimuma, kuni tasumise p&auml;evani, viimane kaasa arvatud. </eesti>
<inglise>Interest is calculated as of the day following the day on which payment or transfer of the tax was due pursuant to law until the day on which payment is effected, inclusive of the latter. </inglise>
<eesti>(10.04.96 j&otilde;ust.12.05.96 - RT I 1996, 29, 577) </eesti>
<inglise>(10.04.96 entered into force 12.05.96 - RT I 1996, 29, 577) </inglise>
<eesti>(1 (1)) Kui maksumaksja taotlusel on temale tagastatud v&otilde;i tema muude maksukohustuste katteks kantud suurem maksusumma, kui oleks tulnud tagastada v&otilde;i kanda vastavalt maksuseadusele, arvutatakse enamtagastatud v&otilde;i enamkantud maksusummalt intressi alates p&auml;evast, mil maksusumma tagastati v&otilde;i kanti muude maksukohustuste katteks, kuni selle maksusumma maksumaksja poolt tagasimaksmise p&auml;evani, viimane kaasa arvatud. </eesti>
<inglise>(1 (1)) If, at the request of a taxpayer, an amount of tax is refunded to the taxpayer or is transferred to cover other tax liabilities of the taxpayer and if such amount of tax is greater than is due to be refunded or transferred pursuant to a tax Act, interest is calculated on the excess amount of tax refunded or transferred as of the day on which the amount of tax was refunded or transferred to cover other tax liabilities until the day on which the taxpayer pays back such amount of tax, inclusive of the latter. </inglise>
<eesti>(10.04.96 j&otilde;ust.12.05.96 - RT I 1996, 29, 577) </eesti>
<inglise>(10.04.96 entered into force 12.05.96 - RT I 1996, 29, 577) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui maksumaksja tasub maksuhalduri ettekirjutuse alusel suurema maksusumma, kui tal oleks tulnud tasuda vastavalt maksuseadusele, arvestatakse enammakstud summalt intressi maksumaksja kasuks, alates enammakstud summa tasumise p&auml;evast kuni summa tagastamiseni v&otilde;i maksumaksja muude maksukohustuste katteks arvestamiseni. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If a taxpayer pays a greater amount of tax pursuant to a precept of a tax authority than is due according to a tax Act, interest is calculated for the benefit of the taxpayer on the excess amount as of the day on which the excess amount of tax was paid until the refund of the amount of tax or the transfer of the amount of tax to cover other tax liabilities of the taxpayer. </inglise>
<eesti>(2 (1)) Kui maksumaksja on taotlenud maksuhaldurilt maksuseaduses etten&auml;htust enammakstud maksusumma tagastamist ja maksuhaldur ei ole seda tagastanud k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahvi 10 2. l&otilde;ikes s&auml;testatud t&auml;htaja jooksul, arvestatakse tagastamata summalt intressi alates p&auml;evast, mis j&auml;rgneb p&auml;evale, mil maksu tagastamine pidi toimuma, kuni maksusumma tagastamise p&auml;evani, viimane kaasa arvatud. </eesti>
<inglise>(2 (1)) If a taxpayer applies for a refund from a tax authority of an amount of tax paid in excess of that prescribed in a tax Act, and if the tax authority does not refund such amount within the term provided for in subsection 10 (2) of this Act, interest is calculated on the unrefunded amount as of the day following the day on which the refund of the amount of tax was due to be effected until the day on which the amount of tax is refunded, inclusive of the latter. </inglise>
<eesti>(10.04.96 j&otilde;ust.12.05.96 - RT I 1996, 29, 577) </eesti>
