<eesti>&sect; 33. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 33. </inglise>
<eesti>Laekumine </eesti>
<inglise>Receipt </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esoleva seadusega kehtestatud intressid laekuvad vastava maksu laekumise kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Interest imposed in this Act is paid into the place of receipt of the corresponding tax. </inglise>
<eesti>(17.02.99 j&otilde;ust.01.04.99 - RT I 1999, 27, 394) </eesti>
<inglise>(17.02.99 entered into force 01.04.99 - RT I 1999, 27, 394) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva seaduse alusel m&auml;&auml;ratud trahvid laekuvad riigieelarvesse. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Fines imposed pursuant to this Act are paid into the state budget. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 34. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 34. </inglise>
<eesti>Tagasimaksete allikas </eesti>
<inglise>Source of refunds </inglise>
<eesti>Maksumaksjale tagastatavad enammakstud maksusummad ja intressid makstakse tagasi nende laekumise kohtadest. </eesti>
<inglise>Refunds on overpaid amounts of tax and interest are paid to taxpayers from the places that such amounts are received. </inglise>
<eesti>VII peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter VII </inglise>
<eesti>Maksuv&otilde;la tasumise ajatamine </eesti>
<inglise>Postponement of Payment of Tax Arrears </inglise>
<eesti>(10.04.96 j&otilde;ust.12.05.96 - RT I 1996, 29, 577) </eesti>
<inglise>(10.04.96 entered into force 12.05.96 - RT I 1996, 29, 577) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 34 (1). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 34 (1). </inglise>
<eesti>(Kehtetu - 10.04.96 j&otilde;ust.12.05.96 - RT I 1996, 29, 577) </eesti>
<inglise>(Repealed - 10.04.96 entered into force 12.05.96 - RT I 1996, 29, 577) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 34 (2). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 34 (2). </inglise>
<eesti>Maksuv&otilde;la tasumise ajatamise taotlemine ja otsustamine </eesti>
<inglise>Application for and decision on postponement of payment of tax arrears </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Maksumaksjal on &otilde;igus kirjalikult taotleda maksuhaldurilt maksuv&otilde;la tasumise ajatamist, esitades p&otilde;hjenduse ja maksuv&otilde;la tasumise ajakava. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A taxpayer has the right to apply in writing to a tax authority for the postponement of payment of tax arrears if the taxpayer presents justification and a schedule for payment of tax arrears. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Maksuhaldur teeb otsuse k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ikes nimetatud taotluse kohta 15 p&auml;eva jooksul selle saamisest arvates. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A tax authority shall make a decision concerning an application specified in subsection (1) of this section within fifteen days as of the date of receipt of the application. </inglise>
<eesti>Otsuse tegemisel on maksuhalduril &otilde;igus maksumaksja esitatud maksuv&otilde;la tasumise ajakava muuta, samuti n&otilde;uda ajatatava maksuv&otilde;la tagamiseks k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 4. l&otilde;ikes s&auml;testatud tagatist. </eesti>
<inglise>Upon making a decision, the tax authority has the right to amend the schedule for payment of tax arrears submitted by a taxpayer and to demand the security provided for in subsection (4) of this section to guarantee the tax arrears to be postponed. </inglise>
<eesti>Riigi- ja kohaliku omavalitsus&uuml;ksuse asutuselt tagatist ei n&otilde;uta. </eesti>
<inglise>State and local government agencies need not provide security. </inglise>
<eesti>Tagatise n&otilde;ue esitatakse maksumaksjale kirjalikult. </eesti>
<inglise>A demand for security shall be submitted to the taxpayer in writing. </inglise>
<eesti>Tagatise n&otilde;udmise korral tehakse maksuv&otilde;la tasumise ajatamise otsus viie t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva jooksul tagatise esitamise p&auml;evast arvates. </eesti>
<inglise>If security is required, a decision on postponement of the payment of the tax arrears shall be made within five working days as of the date of the provision of security. </inglise>
<eesti>(12.04.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.04.2000 entered into force 01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Maksuv&otilde;la tasumise ajatamise taotlus j&auml;etakse rahuldamata, kui: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An application for postponement of the payment of tax arrears shall be denied if: </inglise>
<eesti>1) taotluses puudub p&otilde;hjendus; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the justification has been omitted from the application; </inglise>
<eesti>2) maksumaksjale on tehtud ettekirjutus maksuv&otilde;la tasumiseks kahe kalendrip&auml;eva jooksul ettekirjutuse saamise p&auml;evale j&auml;rgnevast p&auml;evast arvates; </eesti>
<inglise>2) a precept has been issued to the taxpayer for payment of tax arrears within two calendar days as of the date following the date of receipt of the precept; </inglise>
<eesti>3) maksumaksja ei t&auml;ida k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 12 1. l&otilde;ikes s&auml;testatud kohustust; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the taxpayer fails to perform the obligation provided for in subsection 12 (1) of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>4) maksumaksja ei esita maksuhalduri poolt n&otilde;utavat tagatist v&otilde;i maksuhaldur ei pea esitatud tagatist k&uuml;llaldaseks v&otilde;i usaldusv&auml;&auml;rseks; </eesti>
<inglise>4) the taxpayer fails to provide the security required by the tax authority or the tax authority does not consider the security provided to be sufficient or trustworthy; </inglise>
<eesti>5) esineb muid seaduses nimetamata j&auml;etud asjaolusid v&otilde;i p&otilde;hjusi, mille t&otilde;ttu maksuhaldur ei pea maksuv&otilde;la tasumise ajatamist otstarbekaks. </eesti>
<inglise>5) other circumstances or grounds not specified by law exist which cause the tax authority not to consider postponement of the payment of the tax arrears expedient. </inglise>
<eesti>(12.04.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.04.2000 entered into force 01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Maksuhaldur aktsepteerib tagatisena garandi poolt v&auml;ljastatud garantiidokumenti, k&auml;endajaga s&otilde;lmitud k&auml;enduslepingut v&otilde;i maksuv&otilde;la tagamiseks asja&otilde;igusseaduses (RT I 1993, 39, 590; RT I 1999, 44, 509; 2001, 34, 185) s&auml;testatud korras riigi kasuks seatud registerpanti v&otilde;i h&uuml;poteeki. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Guarantee documents issued by a guarantor, contracts of suretyship entered into with a surety, and registered securities over movables or mortgages established for the benefit of the state pursuant to the procedure provided for in the Law of Property Act (RT I 1993, 39, 590; RT I 1999, 44, 509; 2001, 34, 185) in order to guarantee tax arrears are accepted as security by tax authorities. </inglise>
<eesti>Tagatise liigi valib tagatise esitaja. </eesti>
<inglise>The provider of security chooses the type of security. </inglise>
<eesti>Riigi nimel kirjutab pandilepingule alla selle riiklike maksude maksuhalduri asutuse juht v&otilde;i tema volitatud esindaja, kellelt ajatamist taotletakse. </eesti>
<inglise>Pledge contracts shall be signed in the name of the state by the head of the office of the tax authority for state taxes to which an application is made for postponement or by his or her authorised representative. </inglise>
<eesti>(12.04.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.04.2000 entered into force 01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Garandiks v&otilde;i k&auml;endajaks v&otilde;ib olla Eestis registreeritud isik, keda maksuhaldur garandi v&otilde;i k&auml;endajana aktsepteerib ning kes garantiidokumendis v&otilde;i k&auml;enduslepingus kohustub solidaarselt maksumaksjaga tasuma ajatatava maksuv&otilde;la eelnimetatud dokumendis v&otilde;i lepingus m&auml;rgitud summas ja ajatamistaotluses etten&auml;htud t&auml;htaegadel. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Any person registered in Estonia who is accepted by the tax authority as a guarantor or surety and who undertakes in the guarantee document or contract of suretyship to pay, solidarily with the taxpayer, the tax arrears to be postponed in the amount indicated in the aforementioned document or contract and during the terms prescribed in the application for postponement may act as a guarantor or surety. </inglise>
<eesti>(12.04.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.04.2000 entered into force 01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Maksuhalduril on &otilde;igus tagatist mitte aktsepteerida ning keelduda ajatamisest, kui garant v&otilde;i k&auml;endaja ei ole tema arvates usaldatav v&otilde;i kui summa, mille ulatuses tagatis esitatakse, ei ole piisav. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) A tax authority has the right not to accept security and to deny postponement if the tax authority does not consider the guarantor or surety trustworthy or if the amount in which security is provided is not sufficient. </inglise>
<eesti>(12.04.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.04.2000 entered into force 01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 34 (3). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 34 (3). </inglise>
<eesti>Maksuhalduri &otilde;igused maksuv&otilde;la tasumise ajatamisel ja intressi m&auml;&auml;ramisel </eesti>
<inglise>Rights of tax authorities in postponement of payment of tax arrears and determination of interest </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahvi 34 (2) 1. l&otilde;ikes s&auml;testatud taotluse rahuldamisel on maksuhalduril &otilde;igus v&auml;hendada t&auml;htp&auml;evaks tasumata maksusummalt, mille maksuv&otilde;lana tasumine on ajatatud, arvestatava intressi m&auml;&auml;ra kuni 50% ajatamise otsuse vastuv&otilde;tmise p&auml;evast arvates. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Upon satisfaction of an application provided for in subsection 342 (1) of this Act, a tax authority has the right to reduce the rate of interest calculated on the amount of tax outstanding by the due date, and the payment of which as tax arrears has been postponed, by up to 50 per cent as of the date on which the decision to postpone is adopted. </inglise>
<eesti>(10.04.96 j&otilde;ust.12.05.96 - RT I 1996, 29, 577) </eesti>
<inglise>(10.04.96 entered into force 12.05.96 - RT I 1996, 29, 577) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui maksumaksja t&auml;idab maksuv&otilde;la tasumise ajakava, ei rakenda maksuhaldur k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahvi 10 3. l&otilde;ikes ja paragrahvides 24-26 s&auml;testatud &otilde;igusi. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If a taxpayer meets the schedule for payment of tax arrears, the tax authority shall not exercise the rights provided for in subsection 10 (3) and &sect;&sect; 24-26 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(10.04.96 j&otilde;ust.12.05.96 - RT I 1996, 29, 577) </eesti>
<inglise>(10.04.96 entered into force 12.05.96 - RT I 1996, 29, 577) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui maksumaksja ei t&auml;ida maksuv&otilde;la tasumise ajakava v&otilde;i ei tasu ajakava kehtimise perioodil t&auml;htaegselt oma jooksvaid makse, v&otilde;i ei t&auml;ida asja&otilde;igusseaduses s&auml;testatud kohustust hoida maksuv&otilde;la tagamiseks pandiga koormatud asja, on maksuhalduril &otilde;igus: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If a taxpayer does not meet the schedule for payment of tax arrears or does not pay taxes which become due during the period of validity of the schedule on time, or fails to perform an obligation, provided for in the Law of Property Act to keep a thing encumbered with a pledge in order to guarantee tax arrears, the tax authority has the right to: </inglise>
<eesti>(12.04.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.04.2000 entered into force 01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </inglise>
<eesti>1) t&uuml;histada maksuv&otilde;la tasumise ajakava; </eesti>
<inglise>1) revoke the schedule for payment of tax arrears; </inglise>
<eesti>2) t&uuml;histada v&auml;hendatud intressim&auml;&auml;r; </eesti>
<inglise>2) revoke the reduced interest rate; </inglise>
<eesti>3) arvestada t&auml;htp&auml;evaks tasumata maksusummalt, mille maksuv&otilde;lana tasumine oli ajatatud, intressi tagasiulatuvalt k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 28 4. l&otilde;ike alusel kehtestatud m&auml;&auml;ras. </eesti>
<inglise>3) calculate interest retroactively at a rate established pursuant to subsection 28 (4) of this Act on the amount of tax outstanding by the due date, the payment of which as tax arrears has been postponed. </inglise>
<eesti>(10.04.96 j&otilde;ust.12.05.96 - RT I 1996, 29, 577) </eesti>
<inglise>(10.04.96 entered into force 12.05.96 - RT I 1996, 29, 577) </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Maksuv&otilde;la tasumise ajakava t&uuml;histamise korral ei saa maksumaksja taotleda tasumata maksuosa uut ajatamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) In the case of revocation of a schedule for payment of tax arrears, a taxpayer can not apply for a new postponement of the payment of the unpaid part of the tax. </inglise>
<eesti>(17.02.99 j&otilde;ust.01.04.99 - RT I 1999, 27, 394) </eesti>
<inglise>(17.02.99 entered into force 01.04.99 - RT I 1999, 27, 394) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 34 (4). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 34 (4). </inglise>
<eesti>T&auml;iendavad s&auml;tted </eesti>
<inglise>Additional provisions </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Maksuv&otilde;la tasumise ajatamine ei vabasta maksumaksjat tema jooksvate maksukohustuste t&auml;itmisest. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Postponement of the payment of tax arrears does not relieve a taxpayer of the obligation to pay taxes which become due. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Maksuv&otilde;la tasumise ajatamise korra kehtestab rahandusminister. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Minister of Finance establishes the procedure for postponement of payment of tax arrears. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Ekspordi- ja impordimaksude tasumise t&auml;htaja pikendamine Tolliameti poolt toimub tollieeskirjades s&auml;testatud tingimustel ja korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The Customs Board extends the terms for payment of export and import charges under the conditions and pursuant to the procedure provided by the customs rules. </inglise>
<eesti>(17.10.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.07.2002 - RT I 2001, 88, 531) </eesti>
<inglise>(17.10.2001 entered into force 01.07.2002 - RT I 2001, 88, 531) </inglise>
<eesti>VIII peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter VIII </inglise>
<eesti>Vaidluste lahendamise kord </eesti>
<inglise>Procedure for Resolution of Disputes </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 35. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 35. </inglise>
<eesti>Maksuhalduri haldusakti vaidlustamine </eesti>
<inglise>Contestation of administrative acts of tax authorities </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Maksuameti kohaliku asutuse ettekirjutuse, otsuse v&otilde;i maksuteatega (edaspidi haldusakt) mitten&otilde;ustumisel on maksumaksjal, maksu kinnipidajal v&otilde;i kolmandal isikul, kelle huve Maksuameti kohaliku asutuse haldusakt puudutab (edaspidi huvitatud isik), &otilde;igus 30 p&auml;eva jooksul haldusakti saamise p&auml;evale j&auml;rgnevast p&auml;evast arvates esitada Maksuametile kaebus. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Upon disagreement with a precept, decision or tax notice (hereinafter administrative act) of a local office of the Tax Board, a taxpayer, withholding agent or third person whose interests are affected by the administrative act of the local office of the Tax Board (hereinafter interested person) has the right to file an appeal with the Tax Board within thirty days as of the date following the date of receipt of the administrative act. </inglise>
<eesti>Kaebus peab sisaldama k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 35 (1) nimetatud andmeid. </eesti>
<inglise>The appeal shall contain the information specified in &sect; 35 (1) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>Kaebus esitatakse Maksuametile haldusakti v&auml;ljastanud Maksuameti kohaliku asutuse kaudu. </eesti>
<inglise>The appeal shall be filed with the Tax Board through the local office of the Tax Board which issued the administrative act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Huvitatud isikul on &otilde;igus esitada Maksuameti haldusakti kohta vastulause 30 p&auml;eva jooksul vastava haldusakti saamise p&auml;evast arvates. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An interested person has the right to file an objection concerning an administrative act of the Tax Board within thirty days as of the date of receipt of the administrative act. </inglise>
<eesti>Vastulause peab sisaldama k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 35 (1) nimetatud andmeid. </eesti>
<inglise>The objection shall contain the information specified in &sect; 35 (1) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>Maksuamet juhindub vastulause lahendamisel k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 38 s&auml;testatust. </eesti>
<inglise>Upon adjudication of objections, the Tax Board shall be guided by the provisions of &sect; 38 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(17.10.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.07.2002 - RT I 2001, 88, 531) </eesti>
<inglise>(17.10.2001 entered into force 01.07.2002 - RT I 2001, 88, 531) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kaebuse v&otilde;i vastulause esitamine ei peata vaidlustatud ettekirjutuse t&auml;itmist, v&auml;lja arvatud k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 20 alusel tehtud ettekirjutus, kuid maksuhalduril ei ole &otilde;igust teha krediidiasutusele ettekirjutust k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 24 1. l&otilde;ike alusel maksumaksja v&otilde;i maksu kinnipidaja pangakontodelt raha vastuvaidlematus korras &uuml;lekandmiseks maksuhalduri pangakontole. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The filing of an appeal or objection does not suspend implementation of the contested precept, except precepts issued on the basis of &sect; 20 of this Act; however, a tax authority has no right to issue a precept to a credit institution on the basis of subsection 24 (1) of this Act for the mandatory transfer of money from the bank accounts of a taxpayer or withholding agent to the bank account of the tax authority. </inglise>
<eesti>Maksuametil ja tema kohalikul asutusel on vastulause v&otilde;i kaebuse esitaja taotlusel &otilde;igus peatada vaidlustatud haldusakti t&auml;itmine, kui ettekirjutuse adressaat esitab k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 34 (2) 4.-6. l&otilde;ikes s&auml;testatud tingimustele vastava ning maksuhalduri poolt aktsepteeritava tagatise. </eesti>
<inglise>The Tax Board and its local offices have the right to suspend implementation of a contested administrative act at the request of the person who files the objection or appeal if the addressee of the precept provides security which meets the requirements provided for in subsections 34 (2) (4) -(6) of this Act and is accepted by the tax authority. </inglise>
<eesti>(12.04.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.04.2000 entered into force 01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 35 (1). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 35 (1). </inglise>
<eesti>Vastulausele ja kaebusele esitatavad n&otilde;uded </eesti>
<inglise>Requirements for objections and appeals </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Vastulauses ja kaebuses peab sisalduma: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An objection or an appeal shall contain: </inglise>
<eesti>1) vastulause v&otilde;i kaebuse esitaja nimi, elu- v&otilde;i asukoht ja postiaadress; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the name, residence or seat, and postal address of the person who files the objection or appeal; </inglise>
<eesti>2) maksuhalduri asutuse nimetus, kelle haldusakti peale vastulause v&otilde;i kaebus on esitatud; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the name of the office of the tax authority which issued the administrative act against which the objection or appeal is filed; </inglise>
<eesti>3) vaidlustatava haldusakti nimetus, number ja selle tegemise kuup&auml;ev; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the name and number of the contested administrative act and the date on which the administrative act was issued; </inglise>
<eesti>4) kaebuse v&otilde;i vastulause esitaja n&otilde;ue haldusakti muutmiseks v&otilde;i t&uuml;histamiseks ning viited seaduss&auml;tetele v&otilde;i asjaoludele, millega ta oma n&otilde;uet p&otilde;hjendab; </eesti>
<inglise>4) a request from the person who files the appeal or objection to amend or revoke the administrative act and references to provisions of law or circumstances which constitute the basis of the request; </inglise>
<eesti>5) vastulause v&otilde;i kaebuse esitaja v&otilde;i tema esindaja allkiri; </eesti>
<inglise>5) the signature of the person filing the objection or appeal or of the person's representative. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui vastulausele v&otilde;i kaebusele kirjutas alla isiku esindaja, tuleb vastulausele v&otilde;i kaebusele lisada esindaja volitusi t&otilde;endav dokument. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If an objection or appeal is signed by the representative of a person, a document certifying the authority of the representative shall be annexed to the objection or appeal. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Vastulausele v&otilde;i kaebusele lisatakse asjassepuutuvad dokumendid ning soovi korral muud kaebust v&otilde;i vastulauset toetavad materjalid. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Relevant documents and, optionally, other materials supporting an objection or appeal shall be annexed to the objection or appeal. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui dokumentide esitamine pole v&otilde;imalik, tehakse vastulauses v&otilde;i kaebuses viide nende asukohale. </eesti>
<inglise>If it is impossible to submit the documents, reference shall be made in the objection or appeal to their location. </inglise>
<eesti>(12.04.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.04.2000 entered into force 01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 36. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 36. </inglise>
<eesti>Kaebuse esitamine ja edasisaatmine </eesti>
<inglise>Filing and forwarding of appeals </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Maksuameti kohalik asutus vaatab kaebuse l&auml;bi, kontrollib selle vastavust k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 35 (1) s&auml;testatud n&otilde;uetele ning edastab selle koos asjassepuutuvate materjalidega ning omapoolse kirjaliku seletusega viie t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva jooksul Maksuametile, v&auml;lja arvatud k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 2. ja 3. l&otilde;ikes s&auml;testatud juhul. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A local office of the Tax Board shall review an appeal, verify compliance thereof with the requirements provided for in &sect; 35 (1) of this Act and forward the appeal together with relevant materials and a written explanation from the local office of the Tax Board to the Tax Board within five working days, except in the cases provided for in subsections (2) and (3) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kaebusega n&otilde;ustumise korral j&auml;tab Maksuameti kohalik asutus kaebuse Maksuametile saatmata ning teeb vastavalt kaebuse esitaja taotlusele otsuse vaidlustatud ettekirjutus v&otilde;i otsus kas muuta v&otilde;i t&uuml;histada. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If a local office of the Tax Board agrees with an appeal, the appeal shall not be sent to the Tax Board and the local office of the Tax Board shall make a decision to amend or revoke the contested precept or decision according to the request of the person who filed the appeal. </inglise>
<eesti>Maksuteate peale esitatud kaebusega n&otilde;ustumise korral Maksuameti kohalik asutus t&uuml;histab selle v&otilde;i v&auml;ljastab uue, parandatud maksuteate. </eesti>
<inglise>If a local office of the Tax Board agrees with an appeal filed against a tax notice, the local office shall revoke the tax notice or issue a new, corrected tax notice. </inglise>
<eesti>Eespool nimetatud uue haldusaktiga mitten&otilde;ustumisel on huvitatud isikul &otilde;igus esitada k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 35 s&auml;testatud korras uus kaebus. </eesti>
<inglise>Upon disagreement with the aforementioned new administrative act, an interested person has the right to file a new appeal pursuant to the procedure provided for in &sect; 35 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui kaebus ei vasta k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 35 (1) s&auml;testatud n&otilde;uetele, on Maksuameti kohalikul asutusel &otilde;igus teatada sellest kirjalikult kaebuse esitajale, anda kahen&auml;dalane t&auml;htaeg puuduste k&otilde;rvaldamiseks ning teha hoiatus, et puuduste t&auml;htajaks k&otilde;rvaldamata j&auml;tmise korral loetakse kaebus esitamata j&auml;etuks. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If an appeal does not meet the requirements provided for in &sect; 35 (1) of this Act, the local office of the Tax Board has the right to inform the person who filed the appeal thereof in writing, grant a term of two weeks for elimination of deficiencies and issue a warning that, upon failure to eliminate deficiencies during the term, the appeal shall be deemed not to have been filed. </inglise>
<eesti>(12.04.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.04.2000 entered into force 01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 37. (Kehtetu - 12.04.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 37. (Repealed - 12.04.2000 entered into force 01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 38. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 38. </inglise>
<eesti>Kaebuse v&otilde;i vastulause l&auml;bivaatamine </eesti>
<inglise>Review of appeals or objections </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Maksuamet vaatab oma ettekirjutuse v&otilde;i otsuse peale esitatud vastulause ja endale kohaliku asutuse poolt saadetud kaebuse l&auml;bi, teeb selle kohta kirjaliku motiveeritud otsuse ning saadab otsuse kaebuse v&otilde;i vastulause esitajale 30 kalendrip&auml;eva jooksul kaebuse v&otilde;i vastulause saamise p&auml;evale j&auml;rgnevast p&auml;evast arvates. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Tax Board shall review an objection filed against a precept or decision issued thereby and an appeal forwarded to the Tax Board by a local office of the Tax Board, make a written reasoned decision on the objection or appeal and send the decision to the person who filed the appeal or objection within thirty calendar days as of the date following the date of receipt of the appeal or objection. </inglise>
<eesti>Rahandusministril on &otilde;igus seda t&auml;htaega pikendada. </eesti>
<inglise>The Minister of Finance has the right to extend the term. </inglise>
<eesti>Pikendamine toimub iga juhtumi korral eraldi. </eesti>
<inglise>Extension is effected separately in each individual case. </inglise>
<eesti>(17.10.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.07.2002 - RT I 2001, 88, 531) </eesti>
<inglise>(17.10.2001 entered into force 01.07.2002 - RT I 2001, 88, 531) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Maksuamet teeb kaebuse v&otilde;i vastulause lahendamisel otsuse j&auml;tta vaidlustatud haldusakt j&otilde;usse, see muuta v&otilde;i t&uuml;histada. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Upon adjudication of an appeal or objection, the Tax Board shall decide to uphold, amend or repeal the contested administrative act. </inglise>
<eesti>Kaebuse v&otilde;i vastulause lahendamisel haldusakti t&uuml;histades on Maksuametil &otilde;igus teha uus haldusakt. </eesti>
<inglise>If, upon adjudication of an appeal or objection, the administrative act is repealed, the Tax Board has the right to issue a new administrative act. </inglise>
<eesti>Maksuametil on &otilde;igus saata asi uue haldusakti tegemise otsustamiseks Maksuameti kohalikule asutusele. </eesti>
<inglise>The Tax Board has the right to forward the matter to a local office of the Tax Board for a decision on the issue of a new administrative act. </inglise>
<eesti>(17.10.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.07.2002 - RT I 2001, 88, 531) </eesti>
<inglise>(17.10.2001 entered into force 01.07.2002 - RT I 2001, 88, 531) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Riiklike maksude maksuhalduril on &otilde;igus n&otilde;uda kaebuse v&otilde;i vastulause esitajalt t&auml;iendavate t&otilde;endite esitamist v&otilde;i suuliste seletuste andmiseks maksuhalduri juurde ilmumist. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Tax authorities of state taxes have the right to demand that the person who filed the appeal or objection submits additional evidence or appears at the premises of the tax authority to provide oral explanations. </inglise>
<eesti>Ilmumata j&auml;tmine ei takista kaebuse v&otilde;i vastulause l&auml;bivaatamist. </eesti>
<inglise>The failure of such person to appear does not constitute an impediment to the review of the appeal or objection. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Riiklike maksude maksuhaldur ei ole kohustatud otsuse v&otilde;i ettekirjutuse peale saabunud vastulauset v&otilde;i kaebust lahendama, kui sama ettekirjutuse v&otilde;i otsuse peale on esitatud kaebus kohtusse. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Tax authorities of state taxes are not required to adjudicate an objection or appeal filed against a decision or precept if an appeal against the same precept or decision has been filed with a court. </inglise>
<eesti>(12.04.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.04.2000 entered into force 01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </inglise>
