<eesti>&sect; 40. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 40. </inglise>
<eesti>Kaebuse v&otilde;i vastulause lahendamisel tehtud otsus </eesti>
<inglise>Decision made upon resolution of appeal or objection </inglise>
<eesti>(12.04.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.04.2000 entered into force 01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kaebuse v&otilde;i vastulause lahendamisel tehtud otsuses peab sisalduma selle teinud maksuhalduri nimetus ja aadress, otsuse tegemise kuup&auml;ev, andmed kaebuse v&otilde;i vastulause esitanud isiku kohta, otsust p&otilde;hjendavad asjaolud ja negatiivse otsuse korral ka edasikaebamise kord. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A decision made upon resolution of an appeal or objection shall set out the official title and address of the tax authority which made the decision, the date on which the decision was made, data on the person who filed the appeal or objection, the circumstances on which the decision was based and, in the event of a negative decision, the procedure for further appeal. </inglise>
<eesti>(12.04.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.04.2000 entered into force 01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Otsus tehakse kaebuse v&otilde;i vastulause esitajale teatavaks ning antakse k&auml;tte allkirja vastu v&otilde;i saadetakse posti teel v&auml;ljastusteatega. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The person who filed the appeal or objection shall be notified of the decision, which shall be delivered to the person against a signature or sent by post with advice of delivery. </inglise>
<eesti>(12.04.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.04.2000 entered into force 01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 41. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 41. </inglise>
<eesti>Kohtusse kaebamine </eesti>
<inglise>Appeal to court </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Riiklike maksude maksuhalduri haldusakti vaidlustanud isikul on &otilde;igus p&ouml;&ouml;rduda maksuvaidluse lahendamiseks kohtusse. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Persons who contest administrative acts of the tax authority of state taxes have the right of recourse to the courts for resolution of the tax dispute. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kaebuse esitamine ei vabasta huvitatud isikut talle haldusaktiga pandud kohustuste t&auml;itmisest, v&auml;lja arvatud k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 20 alusel tehtud ettekirjutus. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The filing of an appeal does not exempt an interested person from performance of obligations imposed on the interested person by an administrative act, except precepts issued on the basis of &sect; 20 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui riiklike maksude maksuhaldur ei tee vastulause v&otilde;i kaebuse lahendamisel k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 38 s&auml;testatud n&otilde;uetele vastavat otsust seaduses s&auml;testatud t&auml;htaja jooksul, t&uuml;histab kohus huvitatud isiku n&otilde;udmisel vaidlustatava haldusakti. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If, upon adjudication of an objection or appeal, the tax authority for state taxes fails to make a decision which meets the requirements provided for in &sect; 38 of this Act during the term provided by law, a court shall repeal the contested administrative act at the request of the interested person. </inglise>
<eesti>(12.04.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.04.2000 entered into force 01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </inglise>
<eesti>IX peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter IX </inglise>
<eesti>L&otilde;pps&auml;tted </eesti>
<inglise>Final Provisions </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 42. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 42. </inglise>
<eesti>Maksuv&otilde;lgnevuste sissen&otilde;udmise j&auml;rjekord </eesti>
<inglise>Order of collection of tax arrears </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Maksuv&otilde;lglaselt n&otilde;utakse esmaj&auml;rjekorras sisse riiklike maksude maksuv&otilde;lad. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Arrears of state taxes are the first to be collected from persons who owe arrears. </inglise>
<eesti>(10.04.96 j&otilde;ust.12.05.96 - RT I 1996, 29, 577; 12.04.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </eesti>
<inglise>(10.04.96 entered into force 12.05.96 - RT I 1996, 29, 577; 12.04.2000 entered into force 01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Maksuv&otilde;la sissen&otilde;udmisel k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 24 1. l&otilde;ikes s&auml;testatud viisil n&otilde;utakse maksuv&otilde;lglaselt esmaj&auml;rjekorras sisse intressid ning seej&auml;rel maksusumma. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Upon collection of tax arrears in the manner provided for in subsection 24 (1) of this Act, interest is the first to be collected from persons who owe arrears and thereafter the amount of tax to be paid is collected. </inglise>
<eesti>(12.04.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.04.2000 entered into force 01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 42 (1). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 42 (1). </inglise>
<eesti>(Kehtetu - 12.04.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </eesti>
<inglise>(Repealed - 12.04.2000 entered into force 01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 43. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 43. </inglise>
<eesti>Maksuv&otilde;la kustutamine </eesti>
<inglise>Forgiveness of tax arrears </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Riiklike maksude maksuhalduril on &otilde;igus kustutada rahandusministri kehtestatud tingimustel ja korras: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The tax authority for state taxes has the right, under the conditions and pursuant to the procedure established by the Minister of Finance, to forgive: </inglise>
<eesti>1) juriidilise isiku maksuv&otilde;lg tema pankroti- v&otilde;i likvideerimismenetlusega l&otilde;petamise korral; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the tax arrears of a legal person upon dissolution of the legal person with bankruptcy or liquidation proceedings; </inglise>
<eesti>2) f&uuml;&uuml;silise isiku (sealhulgas f&uuml;&uuml;silisest isikust ettev&otilde;tja) maksuv&otilde;lg tema surma v&otilde;i surnuks tunnistamise korral, juhul kui puudub p&auml;randvara, millele sissen&otilde;uet p&ouml;&ouml;rata, v&otilde;i osas, mis &uuml;letab inventeeritud p&auml;randvara maksumust, millest on vastavalt p&auml;rimisseaduse &sect;-s 134 s&auml;testatule rahuldatud eelmiste j&auml;rjekohtade n&otilde;uded. </eesti>
<inglise>2) the tax arrears of a natural person (including a sole proprietor) upon the death or declaration of death of the natural person, if no estate exists which could be subject to a claim for payment, or to the extent exceeding the value of the inventorised estate from which claims with higher ranking have been satisfied pursuant to the provisions of &sect; 134 of the Law of Succession Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Vabariigi Valitsusel on &otilde;igus riigi &auml;ri&uuml;hingu erastamisel rahandusministri ettepanekul kustutada erastatava &auml;ri&uuml;hingu maksuv&otilde;lg v&otilde;i ajatada maksuv&otilde;la tasumine. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Upon privatisation of a state company and on the proposal of the Minister of Finance, the Government of the Republic has the right to forgive the tax arrears or postpone payment of the tax arrears of such company. </inglise>
<eesti>Maksuv&otilde;la kustutamise ja ajatamise korra kehtestab rahandusminister. </eesti>
<inglise>The procedure for forgiveness and postponement of the payment of tax arrears shall be established by the Minister of Finance. </inglise>
<eesti>Erastamisel olevaks &auml;ri&uuml;hinguks k&auml;esoleva seaduse t&auml;henduses loetakse erastamisnimekirja kinnitatud &auml;ri&uuml;hingut enne erastamise ostu-m&uuml;&uuml;gilepingu s&otilde;lmimist. </eesti>
<inglise>For the purposes of this Act, a company being privatised is deemed to be a company which is approved on the privatisation list but the privatisation contract for the purchase and sale of the enterprise has not been entered into. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Erastatava &auml;ri&uuml;hingu maksuv&otilde;la tasumise ajatamisel kehtestatakse intressi suurus ja selle tasumise kord Vabariigi Valitsuse korraldusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Upon postponement of the payment of the tax arrears of a company being privatised, the amount of interest and the procedure for payment thereof shall be established by an order of the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>(12.04.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.04.2000 entered into force 01.06.2000 - RT I 2000, 35, 216) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 43 (1). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 43 (1). </inglise>
<eesti>Enne k&auml;esoleva seaduse j&otilde;ustumist kehtinud maksuseadustega etten&auml;htud maksude m&auml;&auml;ramine ja sissen&otilde;udmine </eesti>
<inglise>Assessment and collection of taxes prescribed by tax Acts in force prior to entry into force of this Act </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Maksuhalduril on &otilde;igus k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 22 alusel m&auml;&auml;rata enne k&auml;esoleva seaduse j&otilde;ustumist kehtinud maksuseadustega etten&auml;htud maksude tasumata maksusumma. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A tax authority has the right pursuant to &sect; 22 of this Act to assess the amount of tax outstanding with regard to taxes prescribed by tax Acts in force prior to the entry into force of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Enne k&auml;esoleva seaduse j&otilde;ustumist kehtinud maksuseadustega etten&auml;htud ja maksumaksja poolt tasumata v&otilde;i maksu kinnipidaja poolt &uuml;lekandmata j&auml;etud maksusumma ning tasumata v&otilde;i &uuml;lekandmata maksusummalt arvestatud intress on maksuv&otilde;lg ning maksuhalduril on &otilde;igus see sisse n&otilde;uda k&auml;esolevas seaduses s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Amounts of tax which were prescribed by tax Acts in force prior to the entry into force of this Act which have not been paid by a taxpayer or transferred by a withholding agent, and interest calculated on amounts of tax outstanding or not transferred, are tax arrears, and a tax authority has the right to collect such tax arrears pursuant to the procedure provided for in this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(10.04.96 j&otilde;ust.12.05.96 - RT I 1996, 29, 577) </eesti>
<inglise>(10.04.96 entered into force 12.05.96 - RT I 1996, 29, 577) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 44. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 44. </inglise>
<eesti>Vabariigi Valitsuse ja rahandusministri p&auml;devus </eesti>
<inglise>Competence of Government of the Republic and Minister of Finance </inglise>
<eesti>Vabariigi Valitsusel ja rahandusministril on &otilde;igus anda m&auml;&auml;rusi maksuseaduse alusel ja t&auml;itmiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>The Government of the Republic and the Minister of Finance have the right to issue regulations on the basis of and for the implementation of tax Acts. </inglise>
<eesti>(26.06.96 j&otilde;ust.26.07.96 - RT I 1996, 49, 953) </eesti>
<inglise>(26.06.96 entered into force 26.07.96 - RT I 1996, 49, 953) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 45. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 45. </inglise>
<eesti>Muudatused varasemates &otilde;igusaktides </eesti>
<inglise>Amendments to other legislation </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Tunnistatakse kehtetuks: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The following are repealed: </inglise>
<eesti>1) Eesti Vabariigi maksukorralduse seadus (ENSV Teataja 1989, 41, 648; RT 1991, 10, 156; 1992, 13, 253; RT I 1993, 28, 500); </eesti>
<inglise>1) Republic of Estonia Taxation Act (ENSV Teataja (5) 1989, 41, 648; RT 1991, 10, 156; 1992, 13, 253; RT I 1993, 28, 500); </inglise>
<eesti>2) tsiviilkohtupidamise seadustiku (RT I 1993, 31/32, 538) 32. peat&uuml;kk. </eesti>
<inglise>2) Chapter 32 of the Code of Civil Procedure (RT I 1993, 31/32, 538). </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Muudetakse t&auml;itemenetluse seadustiku (RT I 1993, 49, 693; RT I 2001, 29, 156; 43, 238) paragrahv 1 1.l&otilde;ike punkti 9 ja s&otilde;nastatakse see j&auml;rgmiselt: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Clause 1 (1) 9) of the Code of Enforcement Procedure (RT I 1993, 49, 693; RT I 2001, 29, 156; 43, 238) is amended and worded a follows: </inglise>
<eesti>"9) maksuhalduri ettekirjutused maksuv&otilde;lgade sissen&otilde;udmise asjades;". </eesti>
<inglise>"9) precepts of tax authorities in matters concerning collection of tax arrears". </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Muudetakse haldus&otilde;iguserikkumiste seadustiku (RT 1992, 29, 396; RT I 2001, 74, 453) paragrahv 21 ja t&auml;iendatakse seda 7. l&otilde;ikega j&auml;rgmiselt: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Section 21 of the Code of Administrative Offences (RT 1992, 29, 396; RT I 2001, 74, 453) is amended by adding section (7) worded as follows: </inglise>
<eesti>"(7) Rahatrahv maksuseaduste rikkumisel juriidiliste isikute poolt m&auml;&auml;ratakse kindlaks maksukorralduse seadusega k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 2. ja 5. l&otilde;ikes s&auml;testatud tingimusi arvestamata." </eesti>
<inglise>"(7) A fine for violations of tax Acts by legal persons shall be determined by the Taxation Act without considering the conditions provided for in subsections (2) and (5) of this section." </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 46. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 46. Entry into force of Act </inglise>
<eesti>Seaduse j&otilde;ustumine </eesti>
<inglise>This Act enters into force following publication in the Riigi Teataja but not earlier than 1 January 1994. </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esolev seadus j&otilde;ustub Riigi Teatajas avaldamisest, kuid mitte varem kui 1994. aasta 1. jaanuaril. </eesti>
